title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients except tortillas and picante.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Put in refrigerator to harden.
Slice tortillas into 1-inch segments.
Serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° when starting to mix cookies.
Whip egg whites, sugar and salt until very stiff.
Whip at least 10 minutes with an electric mixer.
Do not overbeat.
Add nuts, semi-sweet chocolate bits and vanilla.
Cover 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Do not grease.
Drop cookie mixture by teaspoonful on foil.
Put into oven.
Turn oven off at once!
Bake 12 hours.
Overnight is best. Do not open oven door until time is up.
Enjoy!

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mixed fruit.
Reserve pineapple juice. Combine juice, pudding mix and instant Tang.
Stir well.
Combine fruit and dressing.
Toss gently.
Chill and serve.
(Serves 6.)

title: banana cookies
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and sugar.
Add bananas, then dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
This makes a soft cookie that's quick, easy and tasty.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix all liquids.
Place vegetables in bottom of pan.
Place uncooked chicken next, cover with liquid.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger.
Layer cheese, pepperoni, onion and mushrooms.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, corn, macaroni and 1/2 can of water.
Add catsup; salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until macaroni is tender.

title: s'mores
directions: You will need sticks for cooking marshmallows and campfire or heat source.

title: carne guisada
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Melt shortening, then slowly brown the meat.
Add chili powder, comino and garlic.
Cook a while longer. Add onions, peppers and tomatoes.
After the meat has cooked a while, add the mole poblano and brown sugar.
If the gravy needs to be thickened, add flour and water.
Cook until flavors are blended, then stir in peanut butter.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in deep pan (greased and floured). Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tennessee sin
directions: Hollow out 1 bread loaf.
Dice removed bread and the additional loaf.
Bake diced bread and the hollowed out loaf until slightly brown.
Mix all ingredients together and place in hollowed out loaf.	Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: 'uala with coconut milk(sweet potato)
directions: Scrub the skin of the 'uala.
Rinse, then cover with water in a pot and bring to a boil.
Cook until tender (about 20 minutes). Cool, peel and slice.
Place slices into a buttered casserole. Mix coconut milk and condensed milk, then pour over potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Uncover for the last 15 minutes.

title: cheese roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Meanwhile, drain and flake tuna; set aside.
Melt margarine, then toss with bread crumbs; set aside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute garlic, onion and green pepper in hot oil.
Add zucchini and cook 2 minutes.
Place in shallow casserole dish.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until squash is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: summer spaghetti
directions: Chop tomatoes coarsely.
Chop onion and olives.
Mince garlic. Combine tomatoes, onion, olives, garlic, parsley, basil, capers, paprika and oregano in a medium bowl; toss well.
Drizzle vinegar over tomato mixture.
Pour oil over mixture.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 6 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and flour in 3-quart saucepan until mixture is smooth.
Add milk to mixture and heat on medium to low heat until it begins to thicken and starts to bubble.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and vanilla.
In medium bowl, line bottom with wafers, then cut a slice of banana and place on each wafer, then cover with pudding until bananas are covered.
Do another layer of wafers, banana and pudding until pudding is used up.

title: potato soup
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes ahead. In a large pot, stir in all ingredients except diced potatoes. After mixing all ingredients stir in diced potatoes. Allow to simmer, stirring frequently. You may add more milk if you prefer it not so thick.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in 1/3 cup butter until brown.
Remove and set aside.
In the same pan, saute mushrooms in another 1/3 cup butter.
Remove and set aside.
Dredge beef in flour and brown in remaining butter.
Add bouillon, salt and onions.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Add tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, sour cream, heavy cream and mushrooms.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skins.
Remove skin; slice about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In a saucepan, mix all remaining ingredients (except crumbs).
Stir over low heat until just heated.
Pour over potatoes; sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fried corn
directions: Remove silk and husks from corn.
Using a sharp knife, cut kernels off cobs, but cut only about half the depth of kernels. After cutting all ears, use the back of knife to scrape out juice and pulp.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat soup mixed with water.
Top with toast.
Add Mozzarella and broil until cheese bubbles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place onions in bottom of crock-pot. Add chicken pieces. Stir together remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken. Cook on low 7 to 9 hours or high 3 to 4 hours. Serve over spaghetti.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple chunks and marshmallows; refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Use foil-covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes, stirring every 30 minutes.

title: raisin pudding pie
directions: Soak raisins in hot water 5 minutes.
Cool and drain well. Mix pudding, milk, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool, then add raisins.
May use instant pudding, then mix all except raisins until thick.
Add raisins.
Pour into baked 9-inch pastry.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Combine egg, gelatin, cornstarch and cold water.
Stir to blend.
Add boiling water.
Blend thoroughly.
Puree strawberries. Add gelatin mixture.
Add yogurt and Equal; blend until mixture is smooth.
Chill overnight or until set, about 4 hours.
Blend again. Pour into dessert dishes and serve.
Makes 8 servings, 1/2 cup each.
Contains 57 calories per serving.
Diabetic exchange:
1/2 nonfat milk and 1/4 fruit.

title: cassoulet
directions: Rinse beans.
In 5-quart saucepot, heat beans and 6 cups water to boiling.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour; drain and rinse.
Return beans to saucepot.
Spray 10-inch skillet with vegetable cooking spray; add chicken, turkey kielbasa, garlic, onion and celery.
Over medium heat, cook until light brown.
Stir chicken mixture into beans; add carrots, remaining ingredients and 4 cups water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: swedish rice hot dish
directions: Fry
beef,
onion,
green
pepper
and celery.	Add soy sauce, mushrooms,
chicken
and mushroom soups.
Prepare rice with water and
let
set
minutes.
Mix with beef mixture. Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 15 minutes with lid on and then 15 minutes with lid off.

title: "microwave" hash and egg brunch
directions: Microwave Instructions:
Combine corned beef, potatoes, soup, 1/2 can onions and the black pepper.
Spoon evenly into 8 x 12-inch microwave-safe dish.
Do not add eggs.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish halfway through cooking time.
Place eggs in hash as before.
Using a toothpick pierce each egg yolk and white twice.
Cook, covered, 5 to 6 minutes or until eggs are cooked to desired doneness.
Rotate dish halfway through cooking time.
Top with cheese and remaining onions.
Cook, uncovered, 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: tamale beans
directions: Cook dry beans until done, leaving slightly soupy. Season with salt and pepper (or red pepper flakes). Add canned tamales; remove paper from them after they get "rinsed" off in bean liquid. Cut them into large chunks in pot. Add cheese and beat until cheese melts.

title: walnut crunch brownies
directions: Prepare One Bowl Brownies as directed, using 4 eggs and omitting walnuts in batter.
Spread in prepared pan.
Microwave brown sugar and margarine in same bowl on High for 1 minute or until margarine is melted.
Stir in eggs, flour and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread mixture evenly over brownie batter.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Roll into balls (the size of a walnut); roll in sugar.
Press or place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool for couple of minutes before removing from the cookie sheet.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in catsup, water, soup mix, bread crumbs and ground beef.
Mix well and bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
When about done, I spoon some catsup on top.

title: butterhorns
directions: Cut margarine into flour with fingers; add egg yolks and sour cream.
Mix with a spoon.
Mix well and shape into a ball. Sprinkle with flour.
Wrap well in wax paper and chill for several hours or overnight.

title: pot de creme
directions: Put hot cream and other ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Put in 6 small cups.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: date-nut pinwheels
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, vanilla and egg; beat until light. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill until firm enough to roll.
Half dough; roll each half on floured waxed paper into 12 x 9-inches.
Spread with filling; roll tightly from end.
Wrap in paper; chill overnight.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: frank and stein
directions: Cook bacon
in
skillet.
Before
bacon
is done, drain grease (save
a little).
Add onion and pepper and saute until tender. Add
pork
and beans and the rest of the ingredients. Simmer until flavors
mix.
Add sliced hot dogs and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve in bowls with a frosted glass of beer.

title: cowboy supper
directions: Put potatoes in a large casserole dish, then beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble meat over beans.
Cover with onion, sliced.
Cover with catsup.
Put lid on.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Don't add water or open.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and Eagle Brand in microwave container.
Cook until the morsels melt (about 4 minutes on High). Stir until the ingredients are combined.
Stir in the vanilla and nuts.
Spread evenly into a well buttered or wax paper lined pan (8-inch square).
Chill until firm (2 to 3 hours).
Cut and store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: anchovy bread
directions: Blend until lumps are gone.
Cover and let set until it doubles.
Scoop handfuls of dough; put anchovies inside handful of dough.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: calico cheese fingers
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, onion and parsley; set aside. Preheat broiler.
Place oven shelf 3 to 6 inches from heating element.
Cut crusts from bread.
Toast bread on one side.
Spread cheese mixture on untoasted side.
Broil until bubbly.
Cut each piece of bread in 3 strips.
Serve warm.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in a skillet.
Combine ingredients in crock-pot. Cook at 180° for 45 minutes.
Then simmer to draw seasoning through to taste.
Chili powder and seasoning of salsa (hot, medium or mild) should be to personal desired spiciness.

title: quick rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine above ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased muffin tin and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate until served.

title: ham busy bee lunch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish, cover and bake at 325 to 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: unbaked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine together.
Bring to rolling boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, oatmeal and nuts.
Blend until all is mixed. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and allow to set.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and oleo; let cool.
Mix eggs one at a time.
Stir in brown sugar and rest of ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: family favorite potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Peel and chop.
(Do not try to dice into cubes.)
Cut up eggs, pepper, pimentos, onions, pickles and celery.
Add to potatoes.
Blend in mayonnaise, sweet pickle juice and salt and pepper to taste.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together in cooking pan; cook over medium heat until thick. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue or Cool Whip. If meringue, brown in oven.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out and sprinkle with more Parmesan.
Return to oven 5 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, 2 sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda, adding to first mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: nutty olive spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk together until well blended.
Stir in nuts and olives.
Mix well.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Very good on crackers and bread.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Add tomato sauce and spaghetti mix. Cook noodles as package directs.
Layer in pan noodles first, meat mixture next, cottage cheese next, then the Mozzarella cheese. End up with meat.
Then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken florentine dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Can be heated in microwave on Medium power until heated through or in oven at 350° until heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir gently.
Place in casserole.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This makes a large casserole.
Serves 10 or 12 people.
The recipe was shared with me by Roberta Shannon.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together; let cool.
Beat eggs, one at a time; add sugar.
Blend well; add chocolate then flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waffle iron.
Bake on low heat as for waffles, about 1 minute.
Lift cookies out with a fork.
Yields about 3 dozen.
May be frosted with the frosting recipe.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon of the sugar.
Let set until bubbly.
Sift flour, remaining sugar, baking powder, salt and soda together into a large mixing bowl.
Add yeast mixture, oil and buttermilk; mix well.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla. Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
(Butter palms of hands.)
Flatten with bottom of glass coated with butter and dipped in sugar.
(Replace as needed.)
Sprinkle with colored sugars. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple surprise
directions: Pour pie filling into 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Spread cake mix evenly over pie filling.
Pour melted margarine over top; sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes. Cal 445; T fat 22 g; 43% cal from fat; prot 3 g; carbo 62 g; fiber 2 g; chol 0 mg; sod 406 mg.

title: corn fritters
directions: Toss together corn, onion, green pepper, flour, cheese, baking powder, salt and a dash of pepper.
Stir in eggs.
Heat enough oil to cover the bottom of a frying pan to about 1/8-inch, then drop in 2 to 3 tablespoons fritter batter and cook 3 minutes on each side.
Serves 4.

title: pina colada cooler
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until slushy. Garnish with cherry.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Wrap potatoes in heavy-duty foil.
Place in coals, turning occasionally.
Cook 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, milk and cinnamon and pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread the dry yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Dribble melted butter over cake mix and sprinkle with nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruity pick-up(fat free)
directions: In blender, place peeled chopped peach or banana.
Add raspberries, papaya nectar and crushed ice.
Blend until smooth.

title: trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and seal in Ziploc bag.
Great for a snack.

title: speedy lasagna
directions: Brown the ground chuck in a medium saucepan.
Drain off fat. Add tomatoes, Italian seasoning, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Spread about half of the sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the noodles.
Combine the cheeses.
Top noodles with half of the cheese and more sauce.
Repeat layers ending with sauce.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: watergate cake(quick, light and very good)
directions: Mix and blend all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornmeal pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine
first	3
ingredients	and set aside.	Mix all other ingredients together, then add to dry mixture just until moistened. Fill
muffin
cups
2/3	full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried macaroni
directions: Melt Crisco in skillet; pour macaroni and onion in skillet. Stir and cook until brown; pour sauce and spices over macaroni and stir.
Simmer until macaroni is tender; add water if needed.

title: coconut potato candy
directions: Combine potatoes, powdered sugar, coconut and vanilla.
Chill; roll in balls.
Set out to dry a little.
Dip in dark chocolate (taste like Mounds bars) or dip in milk chocolate (taste like Almond Joy; press almonds on top before dipping).
Don't make on rainy or humid days.

title: anne martin's cake
directions: Sift flour and cream of tartar together.
Cream sugar and Crisco well and add eggs, flour and buttermilk alternately.
Put soda in 1 1/2 teaspoons warm water when you start the cake.
Let set until cake is mixed and add.
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and marshmallows.
Set aside.
Melt butter with cocoa and Coke and pour over sugar/flour mixture.
Beat eggs. Mix with buttermilk, vanilla and baking soda; add to mixture. Batter will be thin with marshmallows floating on top.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and onion dip.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef and taco seasoning as directed on package.
Spread over cream cheese mixture after allowing to cool. Spread layer of diced lettuce, layer of shredded cheese and layer of diced tomatoes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy with taco chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill for several hours.

title: pumpkin oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put everything into bowl and stir by hand until well mixed.
Place batter into about 18 muffin cups. Let set about 5 minutes, then place in oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: chocolate sheath cake with frosting
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Set aside.
Bring oleo, shortening, cocoa and water to a rapid boil in a saucepan.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add rest of the ingredients. Mix well.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar for about 10 or 15 minutes.
While that is mixing, sift flour, cocoa and salt together 3 times; set aside. Beat eggs well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla to sugar and oil; continue mixing.
Alternately add buttermilk and flour mixture until all is used.
Mix this until well blended.
Add food coloring, mix with a spoon only until it is mixed enough not to splatter; then continue to mix with mixer until it is well blended.
Dissolve soda in vinegar and fold into batter.
Put wax paper on bottom of 3 pans; then grease and flour sides of pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in nonstick skillet.
Add liquids and cook over low heat until dough becomes thick and pulls away from pan. Knead the dough, cool and place in airtight container.

title: calico dip
directions: In bowl, mix sour cream and salad dressing.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight before serving. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: haystack cookies(no bake)
directions: Cook sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk slowly until sugar is melted. Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Add oats and mix until all coated. Drop while hot by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cookies will set firmly when cool.

title: zucchini yeast rolls
directions: Combine zucchini, sugar, salt and shortening with milk.
Heat to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to milk mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Dough will be soft.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Knead and shape into pan rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
They freeze well.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix with enough milk to a good corn bread texture. Pour in greased pan and bake until done at 350°, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Heat milk, shortening and sugar to lukewarm; dissolve yeast in water.
Add to cooled milk mixture.
Add baking powder, salt, soda and flour.
Add enough additional flour to make stiff dough.
Let rise to double; knead and add flour if needed.
Shape into rolls. Put in lightly greased muffin tins; let rise again.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Brush rolls with melted butter while hot.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell and cover with top crust.
Brush with milk lightly and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut slits in top crust and bake at 425 F for approx 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quiche
directions: Prepare crust and line pan.
Spread with beaten eggs with pastry brush and bake for 5 minutes at 500°.
Saute onions in butter until golden, season with salt and pepper.
Put zucchini on bottom with onions.
Toss flour and cheese together.
Spread on top of zucchini.
Pour milk and eggs on top.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes and then for 30 minutes at 325° or until knife comes clean.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain juice from blueberries and pineapple.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat until boiling.
Add jello to this hot juice. Stir.
Add 1 cup ice cubes.
Add fruit.
After this jells, mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup mixture and add sour cream.
Spread on top of jello.

title: katie's lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix in spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce and Ragu spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add Ricotta cheese.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package. Layer noodles and sauce mixture in lasagna dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: crab enchiladas
directions: In small saucepan, combine the cream cheese, Jack cheese and milk.
Cook over medium-high for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese are melted, stirring often.
Meanwhile, drain, flake and remove the cartilage from crab.
Stir crab into cheese mixture.
Continue cooking and stirring occasionally until heated through.
tags: soft style cream cheese with chives

title: hot rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco, stirring until Crisco is dissolved.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Stir flour to make a soft dough.
Rub large container with Crisco, pour dough into container and cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except jelly and catsup.
Make meatballs. Brown meatballs in frying pan or oven for 30 minutes at 375°. Heat jelly and catsup.
Serve meatballs with toothpicks to dip into sauce.

title: 7 layer cookies(also known as killer cookie bars)
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Mix in graham cracker crumbs.
Pat down until all of pan is covered.
Then layer the other ingredients on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut.
Remove from pan or they will stick.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cube chicken and mix all ingredients, but cheese, chips and bread crumbs.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chips and bread crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sour cream pound cake #2
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, adding sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.	Dissolve soda in sour cream and
add alternately
with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 310° for about 2 hours or bake as 2 loaves for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potatoes cilantro
directions: Peel potatoes; wash and cut into small squares.
Deep fry. Wash cilantro.
Chop it fine; beat garlic.
Mix all ingredients together, then add lemon juice.
Serve.

title: jewish-style potato pancakes
directions: Grate the potatoes and onion together into a stainless steel bowl; toss with the lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Place the potato mixture in a china cap or strainer and squeeze out the liquid.
Drain well.
Return the mixture to a bowl and add the remaining ingredients except for the oil.
Blend the mixture well and allow to stand for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sliced salad
directions: Alternate one slice of cheese, one slice of tomato, one or two large basil leaves.

Sprinkle all with minced garlic. Drizzle olive oil, a scant amount of balsamic vinegar and ground black pepper. Refrigerate for a few hours to let flavors mingle. Serve cold or at room temperature as an appetizer or a side salad.

title: pan fried frog legs
directions: Cut a squirrel into pieces, place in a big soup pot with enough hot water to cover.
Let simmer slowly until tender. Season with salt and plenty of black pepper.
Let come to a rolling boil and add dumplings.
Cover and cook 10 minutes. Uncover and add one cup of milk in which a tablespoon of flour has been dissolved.

title: chicken curry(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Saute chicken and onion in margarine and spices.
Add all remaining ingredients.
(Add chicken stock as needed if the curry sauce gets too dry.)
Bring sauce to boil. Reduce and simmer until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and boil until soft.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Place slices of oleo over potatoes.
Add mushroom soup.
Chop cheese and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potato bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Mix well the first 8 ingredients.
Put in pan.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on a large pizza pan and bake at 350° until set.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread over cooked cookie crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese mixture.
Spoon fruit from pie filling and drop on cream cheese also.
Spread filling over top of all fruit as a glaze.

title: pretzel pineapple salad
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar.
Mix in pretzels.	Bake at 400° 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Break apart if needed.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.

title: herb chicken ros
directions: Coat chicken in mixture of flour, garlic salt and paprika. In a frying pan, melt butter and shortening over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning until brown on all sides.
Sprinkle basil and rosemary on chicken; add wine.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 25 minutes or until fork-tender.
Remove chicken and place in serving container.
Skim any excess fat from frying pan.
Mix cornstarch and water; add to liquid in frying pan, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Stir in sour cream and pour on chicken.

title: carrot-apple salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.

title: cream of parsley soup
directions: After
blending
soup, add parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes. Allow to set 1/2 hour and serve.

title: avgolemono soup
directions: Heat the stock.
Beat the eggs well.
Slowly add the lemon juice to the eggs, beating constantly (about 3 to 5 minutes). Slowly add 1 cup hot stock, mixing constantly.
Pour into the pot of soup.
Continue to stir the soup or gently shake the pot until the soup thickens slightly (about 3 minutes).

title: steak fondue
directions: Put one
stick of oleo in fondue pot with one bottle of Crisco oil and a dash of salt.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt in bowl.
Cut 1/4 cup shortening with a pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle ice water, one tablespoon at a time.
Toss with fork until moistened.
Gently press dough into 4-inch circle balls.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Bring broth to a boil in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add potatoes; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add carrots and onions.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add peas; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup of flour, remaining 1/2 teaspoon of salt, poultry seasoning, pepper and milk in saucepan.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken casserole and set aside.
Roll out dough; place crust over casserole and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: michelle's watergate delight dessert
directions: In large bowl add Cool Whip, dry pistachio instant pudding and pineapple.
Mix ingredients together.
Add pecans and coconut (optional).
Keep in refrigerator.
About 2 or 3 hours before serving, add marshmallows.
Mix.
Put back in refrigerator. Enjoy.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix with mixer the first 6 ingredients.
Slice cake and put in long dish.
Pour mixture over cake and top with cherries.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Brown ground beef. Cook your rice. After this is done mix with other ingredients in the crock pot. Cook until hot.

title: dessert
directions: Put vanilla wafers, nuts and oleo in bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Spread over wafer crust the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip, all mixed together.
Chill.
Whip pudding and milk together and spread over cheese mixture.
Top with more Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with garlic powder; pour off fat.
Combine tomato sauce, onion and spices with beef; simmer for 1 hour.
While simmering, cook 8 pieces of lasagna; cool.
Layer lasagna, sauce, Parmesan, Mozzarella and Ricotta in order.
Do not put any Mozzarella or Ricotta on the top layer.
Bake at 325° until bubbling in the middle (about 1/2 hour).
Remove from oven; cover the top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 325° until golden.
Eat and pig out.
Serve with garlic bread and Caesar salad.

title: crispy cobbler
directions: Place butter in an 8 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place in a warm oven to melt butter.
In a bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the milk and blend until smooth.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cornmeal yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk; cool to 105° to 115°.
Combine cornmeal and 1 cup boiling water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 10 minutes. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in medium mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add scalded milk, butter, sugar, egg yolks and salt to yeast mixture; blend well.
Gradually add to cornmeal, stirring well.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add all ingredients except ginger ale and strawberries.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup on top of stove.
In separate pan, boil chicken until tender.
Boil broccoli until tender.
Put shredded chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with broccoli.
Pour cheese mixture over top.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: smores
directions: Break Hershey bars in half.
Place the bars on the cracker squares.
Place marshmallows on top.
Put on a microwave-safe dish.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds.

title: easy apple dumpling
directions: Peel and quarter the apples.
Wrap one roll around each of the quartered apples.
Place in a buttered 8-inch baking dish.
Make the syrup of sugar, water and butter; just let the mixture come to a boil.
Pour the syrup over the apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda, vanilla, nuts and mashed bananas.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Wash tomatoes; cut out cores and cut unpeeled.
Put in heavy pot; add bay leaves and bring to a boil.
Remove bay leaves and put tomatoes through colander or ricer, juicer.
Put onions and celery with a small amount of tomato juice and blend until smooth. Add to strained tomatoes.
Mix 1 cup flour and sugar and small amount of tomato juice.
Add tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes; pour into jars and seal. Process 10 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken pieces in water to cover until falls from bone. Remove from liquid, reserving liquid. Debone chicken. Bring liquid to boil. Mix biscuit mix and milk. Drop by teaspoons into boiling liquid. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam cut up broccoli for 5 minutes.
Slice Velveeta over broccoli; set aside.
Add bouillon cubes to broccoli and water. Brown onion in margarine until golden.
Add flour; brown a little. Add milk to make sauce.
Add to broccoli-cheese mixture; heat together.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze juice and pulp out of citrus fruits.
Add with sugar and water.
Serve cold.

title: corn salad
directions: Add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: fried gruyere
directions: Combine the egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Dip the cheese in the mixture, then into bread crumbs; repeat.
Heat the batter in a skillet and fry the dipped cheese until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Take crackers and crumble 1/2 box on bottom of sheet cake pan.
Cover with chicken mixture.
Top with 1/2 box crumbled crackers.
Melt margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white trash
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir in cereal and coat well.
Stir gently.
Put powdered sugar in a white kitchen trash bag (clean of course).
Pour in cereal mixture.
Shake gently.
Refrigerate.

title: beef roast with gravy
directions: Place onion soup mix on top of heavy-duty aluminum foil. (Piece big enough to cover roast well and fold at the ends to prevent juice from escaping.)
Place roast on top of onion soup and cream of mushroom soup on top of roast.
Place in oven in baking pan and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Unfold foil and both soups will have combined with juice from roast to make a nice mushroom gravy.

title: salmon puppies
directions: Mix salmon, flour, meal and eggs together in bowl with spoon, then add just enough water until moistened enough to drop.
Use enough cooking oil to deep fry.
Drop in hot oil 1/2 spoon size (about 7 to 10 balls) and cook until golden brown.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: In a high sided bowl, break up 1/2 chocolate cake.
Pour on 1/8 cup of Kahlua, 1 box of chocolate pudding (prepared), 1/2 of Cool Whip and 1/2 of crushed Skor bars (sprinkled).
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip and Skor bars.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal pineapple cookies
directions: Mix soft margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla in a large bowl. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to mixture.
Add pineapple and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put
rice
in
slightly
greased
casserole
dish.
Mix chicken with onion and
salt
and
pepper to taste.
Pour this mixture over the rice.
Beat the eggs in broth and pour liquid over chicken.
Cover
with	bread
crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes or until browned.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into Pyrex dish.
Slice onions over top of potatoes.
Spoon hamburger over onions and pour tomato soup evenly over mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: shrimp scampi primavera
directions: Cook pasta as directed and drain.

title: chocolate coconut mound cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Mix butter, Coke and cocoa and pour into flour mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in deep baking pan at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13 inch pan. When removed from oven and still hot, spread 1 jar marshmallow creme on top and cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Fold in shrimp. Refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Cream until smooth.
Add lemon juice and onion; blend well.
Gradually blend in sour cream.
Chill.
Serve with potato chips, crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown sirloin strips, a few pieces at a time, in hot oil. Take all meat out of pan and cook onions or onion soup in oil until tender (add oil if necessary).
Put meat back in pan with onions.
Add consomme and liquid from mushrooms.
Add lemon juice, wine, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add 1 can mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Stir well.
Turn heat to low and add 1 cup sour cream.
Stir in cooked noodles.

title: cheese biscuit
directions: Mix cheese and butter together, mash, then cream thoroughly, add flour to mixture and mix well.
Add paprika for color.
Shape into logs and chill.
Slice thin and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and center with almond slivers.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
This may be prepared in advance.
Freezes well.

title: chicken and artichoke casserole(yields six servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut mushrooms in large pieces. Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika; brown in butter and place in 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Saute mushrooms in butter. Sprinkle flour over mushrooms.
Stir in chicken broth and sherry. Cook on medium heat 4 to 5 minutes.
Arrange artichoke hearts over chicken; pour mushroom sauce over all.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Just before serving, garnish with olives and pimentos.

title: martha's tortilla soup
directions: Place chicken broth in a large saucepan over high heat.
Bring to a boil.
Meanwhile crush tomatoes and add to broth.
Stir in cumin, garlic, salt, pepper and corn.
Dissolve cornstarch in cool water.
Stir cornstarch into soup and simmer for 10 minutes or until thickened.
Mix in cheese, stirring constantly, until melted and smooth.
Do not allow to boil again.
Keep warm.

title: dorothy's cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour.
Add whipping cream; fold in vanilla. Bake at 300°.
Start in cold oven.
Use Bundt pan, if desired.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook meat just until redness has left.
Layer meat, potatoes and onions in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour soup and milk over all.
Salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: french apple pie
directions: *I use the ones in the refrigerator section in the red box.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix Karo syrup, sugar, eggs, cake mix, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Pour over baked crust and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: skillet steak 'n potatoes
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Cut into bite size pieces. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge steak in flour mixture and brown in hot oil.
In saucepan, combine beef broth and water. Add brown steak to this.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Turn meat and then top with potatoes and onions.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate.
Combine with brown sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts. Chill dough (overnight is best).

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, salt, black pepper, crushed red pepper, dried parsley, sweet basil, onion, and green pepper and simmer for 1 hour.
In a small kettle, mix tomato paste and oil.
Simmer until oil is absorbed and then add to the sauce mixture.
Also add cooked sausage at this time and continue to simmer for about 2 1/2 - 3 hours on the stove top or approximately 5 hours or more in a crock pot.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot, including bacon and drippings.
Cook on low for 4 hours.
Check during cooking to be sure they are not dry; if so add a little water.

title: nach0 snacks
directions: Brown ground beef, crumbled.
Cook refried beans in pan on stove until heated through.
Lay chips out singly on cookie sheet. Put small amount of cooked beef on top of each chip.
Put refried beans on each one on top of beef.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of beans.
Broil in oven until cheese melts.

title: low country boil
directions: Bring an extra large pot or propane cooker pot of water to boil.
Add spices, hot sauce, lemon, onion and red potatoes. After ten minutes, add the corn.
After ten more minutes, add the beef sausage.
After five more minutes, add the shrimp and boil for an additional five minutes.
Strain and serve.
Serves approximately 8.

title: no bake strawberry cake
directions: Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip by hand.
Tear angel food cake into pieces.
Stir cheese mixture into cake pieces.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put strawberries in glaze and spread on top of cake mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix rice, onion soup and water well in a casserole dish. Season pork chops and place on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla until creamy. Gradually add confectioners sugar until fluffy.
If necessary, add milk or cream to reach spreading consistency with electric mixer. Stir in nuts by hand.
Frosts three 9-inch layers.

title: tasty cake peanut butter bars
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, soda, vanilla, milk, oil and salt.
Add flour a little at a time.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While cake is hot, spread with peanut butter.
Refrigerate until peanut butter hardens.
Melt Hershey bars in pan and spread on cake.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Cut at room temperature.
Use a big cookie sheet pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put in large pot and pour enough water over it to cover good.
Add garlic and onion and boil until meat is tender.
Add sauce and package of chili mix; cook about 20 to 30 minutes longer, depending on how hungry you are and how it tastes.
Add salt and/or black pepper according to your taste.

title: refrigerator jam 1-2-3
directions: Mix together rhubarb and sugar and let set overnight.
The next day, boil rhubarb and sugar at a hard boil for 3 minutes and immediately add jello; stir until jello is well dissolved.
Cool and keep in refrigerator.
Good for a month plus!
If you desire, add a few cut strawberries the last minute of boiling rhubarb.

title: chicken noodle hot dish
directions: Cook celery and onion in chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown.

title: mary's rice casserole
directions: Wash rice and drain well.
Melt butter over low heat in large pan. Add onion and cook slowly until soft, but not brown. Stir in rice and mix well. Add chicken stock and bring to a
boil. Season to taste.
Pour in a large casserole. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven. Do not remove foil and set aside.

title: black walnut cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together sugar and margarine. Add eggs, vanilla, and lemon extract.
Mix well in flour and walnuts. Beat until well blended.
Add oil and beat about 5 minutes.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in 325 degree oven for one hour and 15 minutes, or until golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let set 5 minutes before turning out of pan. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, or top with your favorite glaze.

title: two apple pie
directions: Combine apples, sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Place in bottom crust.
Dot with oleo.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edges. Vent crust by cutting small slits in top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown and apples are tender.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add butter or margarine.
With mixer at low speed, gradually pour 2 cups hot tap water into the dry ingredients.
Add egg; increase speed to medium.
Beat 2 minutes (scrape bowl).
Beat in 3/4 cup flour for 2 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups or enough to make a thick dough.
Knead dough 10 minutes.
Shape into ball and put in greased bowl.
Make sure top of dough is greased.
Let rise until doubled in size. Shape into rolls.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 450° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: gail's blueberry cake
directions: Mix sugar with cinnamon and set aside.
You can use 1 quart blueberries with 3 large Granny Smith apples, if you wish.

title: moms punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl to soften for approximately 20 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir.
Mash sherbet in a little.
Makes a punch bowl full.
Can add more sherbet for even more creamy, great flavor.

title: shish kabob marinade(beef)
directions: Heat to boiling and marinate overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix melted butter with next 5 ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Mix 2 1/2 tablespoons butter with last 3 ingredients and sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yeast rolls(lawton public schools)
directions: Place all dry ingredients in mixer bowl.
Using a dough hook, blend on low speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Add oil and blend on low speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Add water.
Mix on low speed for 1 minute.
Change to medium speed and knead dough for 8 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place dough in warm area (about 90°) for 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch down dough to remove air bubbles.
Form by pinching off 2 ounce pieces and shape.
Place rolls on lightly oiled sheet pans.
Place in warm area until double in size, 30 to 50 minutes.
Makes 50.

title: fast fajitas
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil and warm in 350° oven for 5 minutes. Prepare beef as directed and cut into strips.
Divide beef and place on top of each tortilla.
Spoon sour cream dip and salsa on each one.
Roll up.

title: squash cakes
directions: Mix and fry in hot grease, 1 tablespoon at a time.

title: super slaw
directions: Mix first four ingredients in large bowl and let stand.
Boil next 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour boiled liquid over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours, stirring occasionally, before serving.

title: cheesy spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add spaghetti and sauce.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add milk.
Make a gravy.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Put 1/2 of spaghetti mixture in casserole. Add all cheese sauce.
Top with rest of spaghetti mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Stirring, add 2 cups water, tomatoes and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour. Add pepper strips and mushrooms.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook beef, drain fat.
Add beans, tomato sauce, salsa, chili powder and garlic powder.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.

title: zucchini toss
directions: Into large salad bowl, tear greens into bite size pieces (about 10 cups).
Toss with oil until leaves glisten.
Add zucchini, radishes, onions and cheese.
Combine vinegar, salt, garlic and pepper; pour over salad and toss.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Following cooking directions on pasta box, add everything and mix well.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Bring vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and celery seed to a boil. Pour over cabbage, peppers and onions.
Stir occasionally.
Cool and freeze in containers.

title: ham fritatta
directions: Heat oven to 325°.

Beat eggs slightly; beat in baking mix, milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and red pepper. Layer zucchini, tomatoes, onion and ham in ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches; pour egg mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake uncovered until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean, 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, nutmeg, salt and milk.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked
pie
shell.
Place
in
450°	oven
for
10 minutes. Reduce heat
to 325° and bake until a knife inserted into the center
comes
out clean, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg.

title: caramel cake icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring often.
Be very careful that this does not burn. Spread over your favorite cake layers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Beat the cream cheese, flour, salt and pepper in mixing bowl with mashed potatoes.
Blend in onions.
Place in a 1-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Put French fried onions on top; return to oven for about 5 minutes.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet; drain.
Combine cheese, sausage and Ro-Tel in crock-pot on medium.
Serve with chips.

title: chile rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; add butter, stirring until butter melts.
Combine sour cream and chilies; add to rice mixture, stirring well.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, mixed with flour.
Add butter or margarine, buttermilk and vanilla.
Cook in uncooked pie crust 10 minutes at 450°; 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir in meat mixture.
Cook until clear and thick.
Add tomatoes.
Stir. Serve over a bed of rice.

title: punch
directions: Pour Crystal Light and pineapple juice into 1 gallon container.
Fill container with water.
Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and butter. Line bottom of unbaked pie shell with pecans.
Pour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pecans will rise to top.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and work off all your frustrations by kneading thoroughly.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Butter the bottom of a small glass.
Dip the glass in sugar and mash down the cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute celery, green pepper, mushrooms and onions.
Add shrimp, crabmeat, cheese and rice.
Make cream sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add all ingredients to cream sauce. Put in seasonings.
Place in buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: beef tips(easy)
directions: Cook bacon, crumble and set aside.
Brown meat in bacon grease.
Add onion, bay leaf, bouillon and bacon.
Cook on low heat 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice.
(Does well in crock-pot.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all except bread.
Pour mixture in an 11 x 13-inch glass dish lined with 1/2 bag of bread crumbs mixed with 1 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle some of the seasoned bread crumbs on top of mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add prepared Dream Whip (prepared according to package directions) and mix thoroughly. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Make a nest in the center of cream cheese mixture.
Pour cherry pie filling into nest and refrigerate.

title: hot rize biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour until crumbled.
Add milk and stir with fork only until dough leaves the side of bowl.
Turn dough on floured board or pastry cloth; knead until smooth.
Roll dough out about 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured cutter.
Place on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade curry powder
directions: Blend all ingredients together.

title: sweet potatoes and apricots
directions: Cook 3 yams or enough yams; slice crosswise to make one layer in 12 x 8-inch flat pan.
Drain apricots and add enough water to make 1 cup of juice.
Mix brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and dash of salt.
Add the cup of drained juice.
Add raisins to juice mixture and bring to a boil.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add sherry and grated orange rind to hot sauce and pour carefully over fruit and potatoes.

title: our favorite chili beans
directions: Saute the ground chuck, garlic and onions.
Add the chili powder. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix remaining ingredients and pressure for 1 hour or more, if needed.
Mix with meat mixture and get ready for a treat.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place first 7 ingredients in shallow dish in order given.
Add salad dressing on top.
Sprinkle with sugar with Parmesan or grated Longhorn cheese. Chill for 2 to 12 hours.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.
Boil until tender.
Beat potatoes, milk and butter until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Bake at 350° until warm.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Mix and cream together sugar, eggs, fruit cocktail with juice, soda and flour. Pour into lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 inch pan. Mix brown sugar and nuts together and sprinkle into the batter. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Spread icing on cake while cake is hot.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding as directed on box.
Mix in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers and bananas and pudding mixture.
Makes a good and creamy banana pudding.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Melt butter. Add eggs, 2 cups cheese and milk to butter and lightly beat. Spray inside of crock-pot with nonstick spray. Put cooked and drained macaroni into crock-pot. Pour egg mixture over macaroni. Top with 1 cup grated cheese. Cover and bake on low 3 hours. Makes 3-quart crock-pot.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat oil.
Cook beef in oil about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until brown.
Add hot water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Stir in remaining ingredients (not cold water or flour).
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Shake cold water and flour in tightly covered container; gradually stir into beef mixture.
Heat to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar, egg, sour cream and molasses.
Add and mix well flour and soda.
Add and mix with spoon raisins and Bran.
Fill muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broccoli, potatoes, carrot, garlic clove, onion, 1 cup chicken broth, salt and pepper until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat.
Put into a blender with remaining broth.
Add light cream.

title: venison rolls
directions: Sprinkle venison with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Lay a piece of bacon on venison and roll up.
Secure with a toothpick or put several rolls on a skewer (for shish kabobs, add cut vegetables of your choice on skewers).
Cook on a hot barbecue grill for 5 minutes.
Turn and cook until meat is done.
(May also put under broiler in oven.)

title: barbecued beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet. Saute onion and garlic until tender; do not brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased 3-quart casserole for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: brisket
directions: Rub liquid smoke into brisket.
Salt brisket with seasoned salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil and place in a baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Cool.
Pour off juice and slice meat thin.
Reheat before serving.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: hot brown cow
directions: Pour milk and coffee into 8 ounce glass or mug.
Add rum; stir and serve.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Put all ingredients into a casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 300°.
During the first hour, stir 3 times with fork, so rice will not settle.
After first hour, you may stir in 1/2 cup raisins, cut fine.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add 7-Up, drained pineapple and bananas. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; chill until firm.

title: apple muffins(from overrock inn)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter.
Stir into dry ingredients, stirring only until flour is dampened.
Fold in apple.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.

title: chicken pinwheels
directions: Saute chicken strips in vegetable oil until done. Roll pizza dough out in a rectangle. Spread out chicken strips lengthwise on dough. Sprinkle with green onions, salt, pepper and Monterey Jack cheese. Roll up from long side of dough. Slice with serrated knife into 8 pieces. Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Serve hot.

title: janet's italian casserole
directions: Cook macaroni al dente.
Place cooked macaroni in casserole dish.
Combine ground beef, sauce, pepper, onion, mushrooms, pepperoni and spices.
Pour mixture into macaroni with 1/2 the cheeses and mix.
Top with remaining cheese.
Refrigerate overnight or bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or microwave on Full power for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ice box cookies
directions: Cream together butter and cheese.
Stir together flour, salt, and pepper.
Add cheese, butter and nut meats.
Make 2 rolls and wrap in wax paper; chill.
Cut into thin slices and place together on cookie sheet.
Bake 325 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cream filled cupcakes
directions: Bake according to instructions on cake box for cupcakes.

title: praline pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs according to package directions for crust, 9 x 13-inch pan.
I usually use 6 tart shells, too; it will overflow, otherwise.
Combine coconut and pecans.
Brown in margarine in frying pan.
Spread on towel to cool.
Combine cream cheese and milk until well blended and smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread 1/2 cream cheese mixture on crust, then coconut/pecans. Repeat layers.
Drizzle caramel topping on top.
Freeze.

title: quick chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites and vanilla until peaks form.
Add sugar and beat until stiff.
Combine crumbs, nuts and baking powder; fold into egg mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 10-inch pie plate.
Before serving, top with whipped cream and fruit. Store in refrigerator.
Recipe may be doubled.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, beat well.
Blend in cocoa.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown beef; drain.
Stir in 1/2 cup salsa.
Spread 1/2 cup salsa in 10-inch pie plate.
Top with 3 tostada shells. Top with 1/2 of each of the bean and meat mixture, sour cream and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with lettuce, remaining salsa and additional sour cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Mix dry jello and cottage cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix together and place in casserole.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, covered.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat in oil until brown.
Fry celery and onion in butter until transparent.
Add to meat along with other ingredients and cook at least 2 hours.
Use low heat.

title: goulash
directions: Cook diced potatoes until almost soft and set aside.
Make a white sauce. Add potatoes and eggs.
Mix.
Put in casserole. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is brown.

title: chestnut stuffing(pastilli)
directions: Soak dry chestnuts overnight.
Drain well.
Cut stale bread into crouton size pieces; mix.
Boil celery, onion and green pepper.
Beat in egg.
Add melted butter and seasonings.
Mix in bread and chestnuts.
Stir well.
Stuff into bird or spread into a greased pan.
If making pan stuffing, bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove cooked chicken from bones and break into bite-sized pieces.
Spread chicken on bottom of long baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and spread on top of chicken.

title: grandmother burgess' refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening together. Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and stir into first mixture.
Add beaten eggs and stir in 4 cups flour.
Then beat thoroughly, but do not knead.
If desired, add just enough flour for easy handling when forming into rolls. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen rolls.

title: mocha walnut cookies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips in microwave.
Dissolve instant coffee in boiling water.
Cream together butter, sugar, brown sugar and coffee.
Add egg and melted chocolate chips; mix well. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Combine ingredients.
Do not add any water.
Freeze some of the mixture for ice cubes.
Add when serving the punch.

title: beef stew bourbonnais
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute until onion is transparent.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in the soup, wine and water.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Add basil, thyme and ketchup.

title: mushroom appetizer
directions: Marinate mushrooms in Italian dressing 1/2 hour before serving.

title: baked chicken 'n onions parmesan
directions: Combine eggs and milk. Combine onions, cheese, parsley and salt in separate bowl. Coat chicken with wet, then dry mixtures. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (covered). Drizzle wine over chicken and cook 5 more minutes, covered.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Pour cake batter into 3 round 9-inch baking pans.
Bake at 325° for about 19 to 20 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes in pans.

title: lime jello salad(mold)
directions: Stain pineapple.
Save juice.
Add water to make 2 1/4 cups liquid. Dissolve jello in boiling liquid.
Cool but don't let it harden.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in blender to mix well. Pour into bowl to harden or set.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onions. Stir until tender. Add salt and pepper, then tomato sauce and chili powder. Simmer for about 25 minutes. Place half the cooked spaghetti in a casserole dish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, part of the Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of the meat sauce, then repeat the remaining layer and sauce. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ruby red tea
directions: Place tea bags in boiling water; remove from heat and allow to steep for 3 to 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags.
Add sugar; stir.
In a 2-quart pitcher, combine tea, juice, lemonade and water.
Mix well.
Chill and serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon.
Serves 5.

title: lasagna
directions: Lightly brown onion and garlic in oil.
Add beef and brown lightly.
Add salt and a dash of pepper, add parsley flakes, basil or bay leaves, tomato sauce and paste.
Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: merry christmas punch
directions: Mix together; chill and serve.
Float orange slices for decoration, if desired.

title: happy holiday cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet with a teaspoon.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen small cookies.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and oleo together.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and mix well to other ingredients.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf parmesan
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place the mixture in a greased pan.
Sprinkle more Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger noodle skillet meal
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in skillet.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Cook noodles by package directions; drain. Add noodles to meat mixture; sprinkle cheese on top, then sprinkle parsley flakes over cheese.
Place lid on skillet.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix the chocolate cake mix as directed.
Fill baking cups 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar; beat in egg.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop this mixture by spoonful into each cupcake and bake according to directions on package.
Serves 24.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in seasoned flour (with added salt and pepper). Melt shortening and brown meat well in skillet.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms; saute lightly.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Combine cream, tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve over hot rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill until serving time.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 2 round pans. Cool until cold.
Slice into 4 layers.

title: holiday pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar in large mixing bowl; add eggs all at once.
Add pumpkin and water, stirring until well blended. In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except nuts and cherries; mix well.
Stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture, a little at a time, until well blended.
Stir in nuts and cherries.

title: no-bake peanut butter bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. In a saucepan, bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over cereal mixture, tossing to coat. Spread into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Cool and cut into bars, 3 x 3-inches. Makes 15 bars.

title: creamy cabbage
directions: Steam the cabbage just until tender. Drain. Add margarine, soup and cheese.
Stir lightly. Spoon into baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and cheese. Bake 20 minutes until heated through at 350°.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Melt margarine or butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place graham cracker crumbs over the butter and press.
Spread chocolate chips in pan.
Spread butterscotch chips.
Spread coconut.
Spread walnuts.
Pour condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake and orange buttercream frosting
directions: Cream together soft butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs; add vanilla.
Beat in dry ingredients alternately with the sour cream. Beat until smooth.
Pour into a 10-inch angel food pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Reduce heat to 325° at end of 1 hour.
Do not remove from pan until cold. Frost with Orange Buttercream Frosting.
Total baking time:
1 1/2 hours.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Set aside.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Add to the cream cheese mixture and stir well.
Layer 1/2 of crushed cookies on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish, then add the pudding mixture.
Top with the remaining crushed cookies.
Chill.
(Gummy worms can be added on top for decoration.)

title: "martha's" casserole
directions: Early in day:
Cook noodles as directed; drain.
In butter, in skillet, saute ground chuck until browned.
Stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese and next 4 ingredients.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Grease muffin tin.
Soak 1 cup Bran Buds in water.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt and buttermilk mixture.
Add Bran Buds soaked in water, additional dry Bran Buds and bran flakes. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain juice from fruits into a bowl.
Mix pudding with juice. Add fruit and 1/2 cup pecans (optional).
Chill all day or overnight.

title: max's mahi
directions: Lightly dust the filets in the flour and place in the frying pan with butter, frying about 3 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan and melt butter in pan.
Add rock salt to taste and chopped Macadamia nuts.
Saute until brown.
Spoon mixture over filets and add lime juice over fish.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Place beans and salt in a saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain, reserving liquid. Combine beans, 1 cup of liquid and the remaining ingredients in a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally (add reserved liquid if needed). Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: glenda gray's casserole
directions: Cook 1 cup noodles until done.
Set aside.
Brown ground meat and drain.
Add soup, tomatoes, flour and water to meat.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add noodles.
Add cheese on top.
Bake in casserole for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: coconut dream cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, butter and sugar.
Mix all dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture.
Add in coconut and vanilla.
Drop rounded teaspoon onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes until slightly golden.
Watch carefully, coconut may burn.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix berries, sugar and the 2 tablespoons flour.
Spoon into pie plate.
Dot with margarine.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half of the potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes; cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
In the meantime, brown pork chops, place on top of potatoes, cover and return to oven for 45 minutes or until tender.
Uncover last 15 minutes of baking.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix butter, vanilla, sugar, water, flour, and nuts by hand. Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: coffee can light bread
directions: Heat milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Add yeast to flour. Pour warm milk mixture over flour and yeast mixture.
Add 2 unbeaten eggs.
Beat with mixture.
Add another 1/2 cup flour and knead on floured board.
Divide in half.
Drop in well-greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Cover with lid and let rise to 1-inch of top of can.
Remove lid.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rose's date nut roll cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 10 to 12 minutes.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and pour over dates (cut up), nuts (optional),
flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Mix together and add to shortening mixture.
Add dates and nut mixture.
Blend until no flour shows.
Make rolls in wax paper; freeze.
Take roll out when you want cookies.
Cut frozen.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve cream cheese in soup.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup of water, then add to soup.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in mold and chill for 4 hours.

title: orange delight
directions: Blend ingredients together in a blender.
A banana can be substituted for the yogurt.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order listed in a 2-quart bowl.
Sprinkle on sugar.
Spread mayonnaise evenly on top to seal.
Place sealed wrap over top tightly.
May be stored in refrigerator up to three days.
When ready to serve, sprinkle cheese, then bacon on top. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Cover bottom of pot with oil; add the bacon fat and butter or margarine.
Saute onion. Add meat. Stir until brown. Add small can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water. Add celery and carrots. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add potatoes and simmer another 1 hour.
Add peas.

title: swiss cheese cutlet
directions: In a deep casserole dish, melt enough margarine to cover the bottom.
Over that, sprinkle the uncooked rice.
Then place chicken breasts on top of the rice.
In a separate bowl, mix together the onion soup mix, golden mushroom soup and water.
Pour this mixture over the chicken.
Cover; bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, then watch for the smiles.

title: 12 day cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and chop pepper, onions, carrots and celery. Stir together.
Make syrup of sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Just bring to boil and immediately pour over vegetables. Chill overnight before serving.
This keeps for 12 days in refrigerator.
Very tasty and handy.

title: amish cake
directions: This may also be put under the broiler, but it must be closely watched as it burns easily.
This makes a very moist cake.

title: chicken wings(12 to 16 wings)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cut wing tips off and discard.
Put chicken in casserole and pour mixture over it.
Let set at least 1 hour. Remove chicken and brown in frying pan.
Put wings back in casserole.
Add 1/2 cup water to sauce and pour over wings.
Top with thin slices of onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered. Cook 1/2 pound noodles; drain.
Add sauce from chicken wings to noodles and mix well.

title: no bake fudge nuggets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand 2 hours at room temperature.
Makes 36.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix hash browns, mushroom soup and milk together in same casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Blend cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold in whipped cream and add fruits.
Pour into refrigerator tray and freeze.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook and drain broccoli and set aside. Saute butter and onion in skillet.
Add Cheez Whiz until well dissolved.
Mix in drained broccoli and place mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Beat eggs well and fold into casserole mixture. Before putting in the oven, add 1/2 cup bread crumbs over top and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice in a bowl.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip; blend thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour and shortening in a medium bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is coarse.
Stir in cheese.
Combine buttermilk, mustard and soda.
Pour into flour mixture and stir until mixed.
Turn onto floured board; knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
12 biscuits.

title: macaroni & cheese
directions: Put the cooked and drained macaroni in a buttered dish. In a saucepan, melt the butter and add the flour, salt and pepper. Blend until smooth. Add the milk slowly, stirring until sauce thickens. Cut cheese in cubes and add to sauce.
Pour the cheese sauce over the macaroni. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4-6 servings.

title: sonora cheese dip
directions: Melt cheeses together in the top of a double boiler over simmering water 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in green onions, red pepper and jalapeno pepper.
Serve hot with chips.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and put in small muffin tins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Immediately after removing from oven, press a peanut butter cup in center of each cookie.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from tin.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine cookie crumbs and margarine; pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Stir in nuts and grated lemon rind.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir with a fork until a ball forms.
Divide the dough in half.
Roll out on floured board; place into pie pans.
Bake at 350° until golden and flaky.
Makes 2 crusts.
