title: quick and easy veggie soup
directions: Add 1/4 inch water to frypan.
Add sausage, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Saute onion in 3 tablespoons olive oil and 2 tablespoons butter on medium heat.
Add garlic to onion.
Put tomatoes in soup kettle and add all potatoes, broccoli, carrots plus onion and garlic when they are soft.
Pour excess water from turkey into kettle.
Slice turkey links into bite size pieces and brown on all sides.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add Tabasco, cumin, sage, white wine and water.
Add turkey to kettle plus add about 1 cup water to turkey pan and swish around and then add to kettle.
Bring kettle to a boil for 10 minutes then reduce to simmer, cover and cook 30 minutes more.

title: chile con queso
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Cut cheese into chunks.
Add milk and cheese in top of double boiler and melt. Stir in sausage and salsa.
(May use hamburger instead of sausage.)

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach about 35 to 40 minutes on low heat, then drain. Mix all; pour into greased casserole.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: lamb on the rod
directions: Place meat cubes on skewer.
Salt meat and place over gas grill or hot charcoal grill.
Cook till
desired doneness.
Remove meat from skewer with pita bread.
Serve with garlic sauce.

title: cheese grits
directions: Boil water; add grits.
Cook until done.
While still hot, add margarine, cheese, garlic salt, salt, paprika, Tabasco and eggs. Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Can be halved.)

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Heat milk to near boiling.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and mix.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; sprinkle nutmeg over pie filling.
Slice butter or margarine over pie.
Bake for 30 minutes or until firm in 350° preheated oven.

title: sour cream salmon loaf
directions: Drain 1/2 can liquid off salmon.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in loaf pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: giant garlic-bread croutons(for a touch of crunch on casseroles)
directions: Preheat conventional oven to 375°.
Cut 1/2 of Italian bread into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
In medium bowl, in microwave oven, cook margarine or butter and garlic on High 45 seconds to 1 minute.
Add bread and toss to coat.
Toss with Parmesan cheese.
On cookie sheet, bake in conventional oven 10 minutes, until lightly browned, turning halfway through cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zesty italian potatoes
directions: Place potatoes into baking dish.
Sprinkle dressing mix over potatoes.
Slice
butter over potatoes.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven until soft or in microwave 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together cocoa, cake flour, baking powder and salt. Add in the following alternately:
milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes exactly.
Cool in pan for about 15 minutes before inverting on cooling rack.

title: sausage shell rice pie
directions: Mix together uncooked sausage, crumbs, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and 1/2 can of the tomato soup.
Pat mixture into 10-inch pie plate like crust.
Combine cooked rice, cheese, pepper and the remaining salt and tomato soup.
Spoon mixture into sausage shell.
Place foil under pan in oven to catch any splatters.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for one hour.
Cut into 6 wedges; garnish with parsley and serve hot.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill and enjoy.

title: cholesterol bomb gravy
directions: Brown meat to a point that "some is crispy"--don't drain grease.
In a separate container blend flour, sugar, spices and milk until uniform.
With low heat on add milk.
Blend and stir thoroughly.
Increase heat and bring to a boil stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add extra milk to consistency you want. Pour over breads - tators - biscuits.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in pan; bring to a boil.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add rice and cook over medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco, beat in eggs, adding vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix soda and flour.
Add to sugar mixture alternating with the buttermilk, beat until fluffy.
Stir in lemon peel if desired.
Bake at 300° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: tuna vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Mix tuna, soups, frozen vegetables and 3/4 cup milk in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Stir remaining ingredients until blended. Pour evenly over tuna mixture. Bake, uncovered, 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown. Let stand at least 5 minutes before serving.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Roll into balls (approximately 1 teaspoonful size).
Press your thumb into top of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Fill thumbprint with jam, if desired.
Yield:
Makes 24 cookies.

title: cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese and butter soften at room temperature.
Grate cheese and mix all together until well blended.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Store in covered container.

title: broccoli cheez whiz souffle
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons of butter.
Stir in flour and water (make like a white sauce).
Blend in cheese spread.
Combine sauce and broccoli.
Add eggs and mix gently.
Cover with crumbs and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: kraut(old way)
directions: Chop or shred firm cabbage heads.
In a 5 gallon crock, place alternating layers of
cabbage
and
sprinklings of salt (about 1/2 cup of salt to	a
gallon
of cabbage).
Do not add water as the cabbage produces its own juice.

title: mozzarella and spinach casserole
directions: Mix drained spinach, milk, seasonings, cheese and flour well. Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with breadcrumbs. Bake at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: macaroni creole
directions: Fry and drain bulk sausage.
Reserve 4 teaspoons fat.
Saute onion and green pepper in fat until soft.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook elbow macaroni minimum time for baking.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mash.
Add onion, egg, salt, sugar, mayonnaise, half of cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Wash sauerkraut several times in colander.
Put in pot, add enough water to cover; add onion and season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Make Zaprashka.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute shrimp and lemon juice in a nonstick pan.
In large frying pan, add garlic, shallots, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper to wine.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until white and firm.

title: pineapple chewy squares
directions: Place half crumbs on bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of coconut.
In separate bowl, gradually cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well each time.
Spread over coconut mixture, then fold pineapple, nuts and cherries into whipped cream; spread over mixture.
Sprinkle remaining coconut and crumbs over top.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: mexican junk
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease. Put beef back in skillet. Combine taco seasoning, beans, and salsa with beef; mix thoroughly. Transfer mixture to 13 x 9 pan. Spread cheese over entire mixture. Place in oven at 350 degrees until cheese is melted. Serve with corn and Mexican rice. May be eaten on soft tortilla shells or with tortilla chips.

title: chicken tetrazzini(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Make sauce of fat, flour, milk and stock.
Cook vermicelli or spaghetti in salted water; drain and rinse well.
Mix in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Adjust consistency with additional chicken stock.
Season with salt and pepper, if needed. Place in greased individual casseroles.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat stirring constantly until thick.
Add vanilla, cool and pour into popsicle mold or paper cup and freeze.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shells or tart shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 320°.

title: shipwreck
directions: Pour soup over all and bake at 325°, covered.
Bake 2 hours. Uncover the last 1/2 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water; add other ingredients and refrigerate in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
This also can be frozen.

title: sausage & cream cheese pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown the sausage in a pan & drain. While pan is still warm, add cream cheese and stir with sausage until cream cheese is melted.
In 13 x 9 x2 baking dish, roll out a package of crescent rolls, flat on the bottom.
Do not break up the sheet of dough. Spoon the sausage mixture and spread it to the edges of the pan.
Roll out the second package of crescent roll dough and place on the top of the mixture.
Bake about 25 minutes until golden brown.
Allow to cool and cut into squares for serving.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil in pan (5-inch pan) and place in oven.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add egg and milk, then stir.
If consistency is still thick, add more milk.
Pour oil from pan into cornbread mixture and stir.
Pour mixture into pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add evaporated milk, milk and butter. Mix thoroughly.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake at 325°.
You must keep a close watch on this pie while baking.
Makes 3 pies.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, but mayo and water.
Add mayo and water and beat 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° in a greased layer cake pan or layer cake pans for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with white butter cream frosting.
This is the deepest, darkest, moistest chocolate cake ever!

title: fruit salad for main course
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Drain all fruit, except cherries and measure.
Use enough water to make cups of juice; add to gelatin.
Add drained fruit.
Drain cherries and add.
Mix well and chill until set.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients and top with onions.
Bake at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in the order given.
Place in bread pan.
Cook at 325° until golden brown.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix lettuce, chicken and green onions; set aside.
Over low heat, saute crushed noodles in the butter until lightly browned. Add sesame seed and stir until both are nicely browned.
Stir often to prevent burning.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: floyd's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Butter muffin pan and fill 1/2 full. Bake 15 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 2 hours; roll into teaspoon-size balls.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet for 20 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain the potatoes and place in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients.

title: baked stuffed potatoes(makes 10)
directions: After baking potatoes and cooking bacon, cut off top of each potato.
Take a spoon and scoop out insides of potatoes.
Mash insides of potatoes and combine with bacon, cheese, chives, butter and season with salt and pepper.
Stuff potato shells with mixture. Place on baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, then flatten.
Put a layer of shredded Cheddar cheese, then roll up.
Put into a loaf pan, folding ends with seams at the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed.
Add bananas and orange juice.
Continue beating until well mixed.
By hand, stir in coconut and nuts.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook onions, pepper and celery in butter until onions are golden.
Add rest of ingredients except rice and cheese, and cook slowly 15 minutes.
Stir in hot drained cooked rice and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot sprinkled with cheese or bacon.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until toothpick comes away clean.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add sugar and eggs. Mix well.
Stir in mashed banana and orange rind.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter. Bake on ungreased sheet at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: creole style gumbo
directions: Add seafoods and okra to the mixture last.
They require a short time for cooking.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk and sugar to rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add chocolate; stir until melted.
Beat over heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat with a whip until smooth.
Very good.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 4 tablespoons sugar, salt and oil. Pour scalded milk over this mixture; cool.

Add beaten egg and mix well. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and 1/2 teaspoon sugar. Add to the egg mixture. Mix in the flour until dough is elastic. Let rise until doubled in bulk. Knead the dough until smooth. Pinch off into walnut-sized balls. Roll each ball in melted butter and place in Bundt pan, coated in butter. Bake at 350° until lightly browned. Can also roll balls in a cinnamon and sugar mixture after dipping in butter.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except Romano cheese and form into a loaf.
Sprinkle grated Romano cheese on top.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt half of almond bark.
Mix with peanut butter and spread on cookie sheet.
Melt remaining bark and chips.
Mix until smooth and spread over peanut butter layer.
Cool and break into bite size pieces.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Mix last 3 ingredients and let set for 10 minutes.
Pour over top.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: tropical fruit pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, cherries and pineapple until thick.
Add banana, pecans and jello and let cool.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate.
Top each slice with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, salt, onion and 1 cup pecans.
Form in ball; roll in other cup of pecans.
Refrigerate overnight wrapped in wax paper.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter-chocolate marble cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside. Combine cocoa, powdered sugar, butter and warm water, stirring until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, water, eggs, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Beat on low for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium for 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of batter.
Pour remaining batter into cake pan.
Combine the batter which was set aside with the cocoa mixture.
Spoon over batter in cake pan. Gently swirl batter with knife for marbling. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.
Sprinkle frosting with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bring to a rolling boil; boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until stiff enough to drop by spoonful.
Drop on wax paper and leave until cool.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand first.
Add other ingredients and place in crusts.
Chill before serving.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Sift flour and baking powder into butter.
Mix in brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple iced tea
directions: In a saucepan bring water to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags.
Cover and steep for 3 to 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags. Stir in pineapple juice, lemon juice, and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 5.

title: sugar cookies and frosting
directions: Cream together margarine, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add salt, baking powder and flour.
Chill well (overnight is best).
Roll out 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 325° until just turning brown at edges.
Frost.

title: mama's swiss steak
directions: Season your cubed steak and flour it.
Fry until done.
Take meat out and put on paper towel to absorb grease.
Put steak in casserole dish, cut up onion and green pepper and arrange on top of steak.
Cut tomatoes up and add tomatoes and juice on top of all ingredients.
Cover and bake for about 2 hours at 250° to 300°.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Put marshmallows and milk on stove and melt.
Cool.
Add to Dream Whip.
Crush graham crackers, then add butter.
Use one layer of graham crackers, Dream Whip, cherries, Dream Whip and graham crackers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package and drain well. Whip butter and cream cheese well.
Mix with cooked spinach.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil. Add the remaining ingredients and beat well. Mix and pour into greased jelly roll pan (10 x 15 with 3/4-inch sides). Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together well and use as frosting for cakes.

title: orzo soup
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery; add to boiling stock, chicken and tomatoes, then add orzo and dried parsley.
Cook about 15 minutes or until orzo is done.

title: graham crackers bars
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a boil in a medium size saucepan.
Cook one minute.
Add next three ingredients.
Mix. Remove from heat.
Pam spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line with whole
crackers.
Pour all of cooked mixture over crackers and spread.
Top with another layer of crackers.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over beans. Marinate overnight. Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.

title: 100% parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with nonstick cooking oil.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Coat with bread crumbs and herbs mixed together.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until tender.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place into souffle dish.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and onion until tender; drain.
Blend the potatoes with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Melt together margarine and brown sugar. Put white sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into fourths and drop into sugar mixture in bag.
Shake until biscuits are coated.
Layer biscuits in Bundt pan.
Pour syrup (margarine and brown sugar) over top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple or peach struedel
directions: Put thick layers of fruit into bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon, mixed.
Dot with lumps of margarine.
Into first 4 ingredients add the egg.
Mix until crumbly.
Put over fruit.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until crust browns.
Serve with milk, whipped cream or ice cream. Yum-yum!!

title: shrimp and fettucini
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, in hot butter, cook shrimp and green pepper with garlic and crushed red pepper until shrimp turn pink.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O together.
Gently fold in pineapple and oranges.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and cream of chicken soup and put in casserole.
Mix together butter, Ritz crackers and poppy seed. Sprinkle over chicken mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into mold.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Unmold.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in large saucepan or pot.
Saute green onions and onion until soft and golden.
Add pumpkin, stock and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring, then simmer 10 minutes if puree is used
or until pumpkin is soft if diced pumpkin is used. Rub soup through a fine sieve or strain if puree has been used. Return soup to pot.
Knead flour with 2 tablespoons butter and gradually add to soup while beating with whisk.
Bring soup to boil, whisking, until it thickens.
Season with curry, black pepper and Tabasco.
Add light cream and remaining tablespoon butter.
Serve, garnished with croutons and whipped cream, if desired.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Cook milk and dates until thick.
Add nuts.
Pour on each cracker.
Bake 8 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls (approximately 1 to 2 inches).
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: tomato surprise
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Mix all ingredients. Adjust seasoning. Butter 5 ramekins and fill with tomato mixture. Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sassafras tea
directions: Take a handful of bits of root for every 1/2 gallon of tea. Boil as you would coffee.
If you like strong flavor, boil until the water turns darkish red.
Sweeten as you like.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sue's yam casserole
directions: Add pineapple to yams.
Add pecans to yams and pineapple.
Add brown sugar to mixture and mix.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes, then cover top with marshmallows.
Bake until brownish color.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Combine veggies.
Spread 1/2 of cheese in pie shell.
Add veggies.
Combine eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt (optional) and pepper.
Pour over veggies.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: scramble party mix
directions: Mix and bake in a large roasting pan, uncovered, at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Combine cheese and oleo.
Add flour, pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into marble size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple whipped cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions and bake in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan for 20 minutes at 375°. Cool. Mix together cream cheese, milk and pudding mix. Spread this mixture over top of cooled cake. Spread drained pineapple over topping. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple topping. Sprinkle with coconut and pecans as desired. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven too 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie, 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: almond roca candy
directions: Boil sugar and margarine 5 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups nuts and cook at 300° or to hard crack stage.
Pour onto large buttered cookie sheet.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut up into bite-size pieces.
Mix together soups, sour cream and almonds.
Add chicken pieces to this mix. Melt margarine, add poppy seed and crackers.
Spread chicken mixture into casserole dish.
Spread crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: rice, ham and pineapple skillet dinner
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add onion, green pepper and rice and saute over medium heat until golden, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth and bring to a boil.
Reduced heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is almost absorbed.
Fold in ham and pineapple; simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve with soy sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kitchen barbecue
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add garlic powder.
Pour in bouillon, barbecue sauce, rice and catsup.
Add peas; cover and simmer on low for 10 to 15 minutes.
While this is simmering, slice wieners and boil them.
When rice mixture is cooked, make a well or hole in middle and top with drained wieners.
Cover wieners with additional barbecue sauce.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add 1
egg
at
a time with flour and milk until all the eggs,
milk
and
flour
are
gone.
Add vanilla.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake
in a greased and floured tube pan for about 1 hour
and
minutes
or until done.
To make chocolate pound cake, add two heaping tablespoons of cocoa to flour.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs. Add flour, baking powder and salt, sifted. Add milk and flavorings. Pour into a tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Spray cake pan with Pam.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Beat egg.
Add cornstarch and mix well.
Add juice from drained pineapple and add water to make 2 cups of juice and water. I add 2 or 3 tablespoons of sugar if using unsweetened chunk pineapple.
Cook in saucepan until thick.
Let cool.
Pour over pineapple chunks, marshmallows, nuts and bananas.
Mix well. Chill before serving. You can add cherries for color, if desired.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Core the cabbage and shred or grate into slaw.
Place in a large bowl and add the sugar, vinegar, pepper, salt and celery seed.
Press together with your hands until completely blended and liquid starts to form in the bottom of the bowl.
Fold in the parsley and carrot (for added color and flavor).
Cover and chill in the refrigerator for at least one hour.
Makes about 5 cups of slaw.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan. Test for doneness.

title: barbecue sauce for hamburgers
directions: Mix and simmer until onions are done.
Pour over meat and simmer for awhile longer.

title: beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Stir in cottage cheese.
Brown onion and beef. Add other ingredients.
Mix with macaroni and cheese. Put into casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Cook until bubbly at 350°.

title: fresh broccoli chowder
directions: Pour chicken broth into large saucepan.
Add broccoli.
Bring to boil; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Add milk, cream, Swiss cheese, ham, butter or margarine and salt. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: pan fried chicken and rice with apricots
directions: Wash and dry chicken parts.
Combine salt, flour and spices and coat chicken with the mixture.
Brown chicken in hot oil in skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown chicken well on all sides.
Add 1/2 cup water around chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Move chicken to side of skillet; add rice.
Stir for 1 minute and then add rest of water.
Add onions, apricots and orange rind.
Mix together with chicken.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and water absorbed.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and dice artichoke hearts; add sour cream, garlic, cheese, salt and pepper. Mix well. Place in a small casserole dish. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cheese log
directions: Scoop out 1 loaf of the bread to make a container; fill with combined ingredients.
Break up the other loaf into bite size pieces to use for dipping.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix wet ingredients together. Mix both together until batter is moist.
Bake 1 hour in greased and floured loaf pan at 350°.

title: mary's banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mixes, milk, Cool Whip and sour cream in bowl. Mix well by hand.
Do not beat!
Sprinkle 1/3 crumbs in dish. Layer pudding, bananas and crumbs, 1/2 at a time, in dish.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: chalupa
directions: Cover all in crock-pot with water.
Cook for 8 to 10 hours, then debone and shred meat.
Serve in a large bowl.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk slowly and make batter.
Pour over melted butter, then spoon peaches gently over this and approximately 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix sugar, cream, vinegar and eggs in small saucepan.
Let come to a good boil.
Cool and then pour over the layered sliced bananas.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare broccoli to package directions, using minimum cooking time.
Drain.
Arrange broccoli evenly over bottom of 2-quart baking dish.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant into thin strips.
Soak in 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add 4 cups water for 30 minutes.
Remove eggplant from water and drain.
Add remaining salt and pepper.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Mix eggs and milk for batter.
Dip eggplant into batter and roll in flour.
Fry in 1-inch fat until golden brown. Delicious.

title: holiday mocha fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar, margarine and salt in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes or until mixture reaches 225°. Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and add next 6 ingredients, stirring until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook hen; bring stock to boil.
Add onion and potatoes; cook until tender.
Add chopped chicken, tomato juice and seasonings. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add corn and butter beans.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Chill milk.
Make jello and put it in refrigerator to thicken slightly.
Add sugar to cream cheese.
Whip jello and mix well with cream cheese.
Whip milk and add to mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top.
Put in refrigerator.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies or 1 (10 x 14-inch) pan or dish.

title: cranberry-pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick pie shell with tines of fork. Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugars and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil hard 1 minute. Remove from heat and add fluff and peanut butter.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Use either smooth or chunky peanut butter.

title: nippy cheddar dip
directions: Place all ingredients in the blender.
Blend until smooth, adding a teaspoon or two of milk, if needed.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Cook 2 boxes frozen chopped broccoli according to directions on box.
Add soup mixture to cooked broccoli.
Add boned chicken.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle 2 (8-ounce) packages Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (about 1 hour).
Serve over rice.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well. Turn into 2 roasting pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans on tray.
Spread sour cream; sprinkle half package of cheeses.
Add crushed olives.
Dice up tomatoes. Sprinkle over tray.
Put picante around the edges of dip; sprinkle rest of cheeses.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Layer apple slices in pie shell.
Mix together apple juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and cornstarch in small saucepan.
Cook on low heat until thickened.
Pour over apples and place second crust on top.
Butter lightly and bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until brown.

title: filled tomatoes
directions: Thinly slice the tops off tomatoes.
Remove pulp and drain top side down on paper towel.
Combine all ingredients and fill the tomatoes with ham filling.
Refrigerate.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Add butter, eggs, milk and 2-cups cheese. Save 1/2-cup for top. Mix all together and put in crock-pot. Cook 3 hours on low. Can be baked in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and bacon in a large skillet until meat loses color and onion is transparent; drain off fat.
Stir in catsup, salt, mustard and vinegar.
Combine remaining ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Stir in meat mixture and cover. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: real good dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Add cheese and soup and heat over low temperature until cheese is melted and thoroughly blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese strata(low-fat, low-salt diet)
directions: Place bread and cheese in greased 5 x 10-inch baking dish. Pour eggs and milk over.
Soak 2 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: raisin apple crisp
directions: Spread apple slices and raisins evenly in buttered baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl. Blend in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over fruit; press lightly.
Bake for 45 minutes or until topping is crisp.

title: brett's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, syrups and butter.
Then add chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; top with whole pecans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: oven-browned chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs and seasonings well and place in pie pan. Mix egg white and water well and put into an individual salad bowl. Spread a small rimmed cookie sheet with aluminum foil and spread the margarine on the foil.
Dip each piece of chicken in the egg white mixture and then dredge it in the bread crumb mixture.
Place on the aluminum foil.
Dribble 1/2 teaspoon oil on top of each piece of chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Turn chicken over and continue to bake for another 30 minutes.
Serves 4.
Contains 215 calories, 7 gm.
cholesterol, 23 gm. protein, 10 gm. fat and 435 mg. sodium per serving.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs and melted butter together; mixture will be very thick.
Spread in a buttered (not floured) 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, melted butter, powdered sugar and eggs until creamy.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O.
Combine pineapple, bananas, strawberries and nuts to Jell-O.
Pour half of mixture in a 13 x 8 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over refrigerated Jell-O.
Pour remaining Jell-O over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.

title: iced tea
directions: Bring water with tea bags to a boil. Pour over sugar and finish filling container with cold water. Stir well. Makes 1 gallon.

title: snowy fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to 234° as indicated on candy thermometer or until syrup, when dropped into very cold water, forms a soft ball which flattens on removal from water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain shells according to directions on box.
Cut Swiss cheese and ham into small squares and dice green and red peppers.
Mix all ingredients together, then add French dressing. Stir and serve.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix everything together; spoon into pie plate. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well.
Marinate at least two hours.

title: old fashion spoon bread
directions: Cook milk, corn meal and salt 5 minutes.
Add butter and egg yolks; set aside and cool 25 minutes.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat in crock-pot.
Mix flour, salt and pepper and pour over meat.
Stir to coat meat with flour.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix well.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in hot oven at 425° about 1 hour.
When cooked, cut slice from top of each and scoop out insides (being careful not to break skin).
Mash; stir in milk and beat well.
Mix in egg yolk, ham, onion, green pepper and butter.
Fold in egg white and refill potato shells.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: fluffy peach cake
directions: About 2 hours before serving or early in day, preheat oven to 350°.
Spray three 8-inch round cake pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare cake mix as label directs, following no cholesterol recipe.
Spoon batter evenly into cake pans.
Bake about 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cakes in pans or wire racks for 10 minutes. Remove cakes from pans; cool cakes completely on wire racks. While cake is baking, drain peach juice into large bowl; coarsely chop peach slices.
To juice in bowl, add whipped topping, pudding mix and chopped peaches, stirring gently to combine.
Refrigerate peach mixture, covered, until ready to assemble cake.

title: chicken with yogurt-tomato sauce
directions: Poach chicken until tender in water with carrot, onion and celery.
Cool chicken.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into chunks. Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onions until soft.
Reduce heat. Stir in flour and paprika.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Add broth a little at a time, stirring constantly while simmering until a smooth, medium thick sauce results.
Season.
Add chicken to pan and simmer until heated through.
Blend in yogurt.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice in top of pepper and remove seeds. Sprinkle inside of peppers with half salt and pepper.
Combine onion, celery, salmon, dressing and bread crumbs.
Mix well. Stuff peppers. Stand upright in baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until lightly browned.
This is just as good cold.

title: try these pineapple squares
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, add pineapple, sprinkle coconut on top of pineapple.
Pour dry cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Melt margarine or butter.
Pour over cake mix.
Cover with nuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°; cool in fridge.
Must be cool before cutting.

title: low country cheese pudding
directions: Take the bread, crusts removed, butter well and tear into small pieces.
Put in baking dish alternating with grated cheese.
Set aside.
Mix milk, salt and eggs (well beaten).
Pour mixture over bread crumbs and cheese.
Let stand overnight (or at least 7 hours) in refrigerator.
Bake in a 275° oven for approximately 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: fried okra
directions: Combine okra, milk and seasonings in a shallow dish.
Let stand for 1 hour or until most of milk is absorbed.
Dredge in cornmeal.
Fry in vegetable oil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave turkey tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into 1-inch pieces.
Cook and drain.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine spaghetti, mushrooms, margarine, turkey, soup and sour cream.
Cook, uncovered, 6 minutes.
Stir and cook 6 more minutes.
Add cheese and cook 2 minutes longer. Serves 8 to 12.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients and place in a greased and floured bread pan (loaf pan or muffins, etc.).
Top with a mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 teaspoon of butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Use garlic salt and powder to season meat.
Drain well.
Add Ragu sauce along with peppers, olives and mushrooms.
Use more garlic salt and powder to season sauce.
Use enough of the Ragu sauce to make sauce correct thickness.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine water and butter until butter or margarine is melted. Put in blender and add milk and sugar and blend.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Equals 1 can of Eagle Brand milk and tastes just as good and works as well.

title: tomato-potato pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread sliced potatoes on bottom. Spread on half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Top with sliced tomatoes.
Put remainder of Mozzarella on top of tomatoes. Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Great with barbecue.

title: stir-fry carrots and cabbage
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add carrots, cabbage, onion, salt, sugar and ginger.
Stir quickly, until ingredients are combined.
Add water; cover and simmer for 6 minutes.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Butter bread and remove crust.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Line with bread, buttered side up.
Spread sausage over bread.
Combine eggs and milk.
Beat well and pour over bread/sausage.
Top with shredded sharp cheese. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender, using additional celery, onion and salt in water for seasoning.
Remove chicken from bones, skin and chop fine or grind.
Add eggs, celery, onion, pickles, sugar, pickle juice and mustard.
Add chicken broth and enough mayonnaise for good spreading.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread and cut sandwiches.
Makes 5 to 6 cups or 70 small sandwiches.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Beat together (in a large bowl) brown sugar, egg and oil until creamy.
Mix in soda, vanilla and milk. Add flour, rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans (8 x 4 1/2-inch). Dot tops with butter and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 325° for 1 hour until golden.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Place sugar in a large bowl; crumble yeast over sugar.
Cover; let set until brown (1 hour to 1 1/2 hours).
Mixture will be brown in spots.
You can tell by the yeast odor.
Heat milk until warm.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add to milk.
Pour butter in and mix well, then add eggs.
Add flour and salt; mix well. Dough will be very soft.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: gene's fish filets
directions: Marinate fish filets in beer for 2 to 3 hours or overnight. Remove and discard beer.
Place filets in a baking dish.
Add pepper and minced garlic.
Pour Italian dressing over; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until done.
Broil for 5 minutes.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Slice chicken into thinnest possible slices.
(This is easier if meat is partially frozen.)
In a small mixing bowl, combine 1 teaspoon cornstarch, 1 teaspoon soy sauce, sherry and white pepper.
Add chicken and blend to coat slices well.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until light and fluffy after each addition.
Mash bananas or press through sieve and add lemon juice.
Beat into cream mixture.
Combine dry ingredients; mix quickly into banana mixture. Add nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan in 350° oven, about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add milk and salad dressing. Pour in muffin pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sauce for fish
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Slice and blanch zucchini.
In a pie pan layer:
zucchini, tomato, Mozzarella cheese, spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese, ending with Mozzarella cheese on top.
Place pie shell on top; crimp edges.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 30 to 40 minutes until brown.
Be careful; pie juices might simmer over.
Place aluminum foil in oven to catch spills.

title: sauerkraut zole
directions: Cut bacon strips 1/2-inch wide.
Fry until crisp; then remove bacon to dish.
Fry diced onion in bacon grease.
Put flour in bowl with water and mix well.
Add flour mixture to bacon grease in frying pan and keep adding water until right consistency. Rinse and drain sauerkraut; then add to pan along with sugar, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Add cooked bacon and mix well. Put dumplings on top and cover and simmer according to package directions.
Cook pork roast as desired.
Serve with dumpling mixture.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl at high speed on electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each well.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until fluffy.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Hard-boil the eggs and shell.
Pat the uncooked sausage around to whole egg.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place in oven at 425° until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes (can deep fry also).
Better than deviled eggs!!!

title: cavatini
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain.
In a large pan, mix spaghetti sauce, hamburger, sausage, pepperoni, onion, pepper and mushrooms. Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: grandma's macaroni salad
directions: Mix the macaroni, celery, bell peppers and onions in a large bowl.
Whisk together the mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper to make a smooth dressing.
Pour dressing over the vegetables, mix well and refrigerate.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: aunt jean's blender cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Pulse blender a few times to break up cream cheese.
Then blend at medium speed for 7 minutes.
Grease (or use Pam spray) a 9 x 9-inch square glass dish.
Pour mixture into dish.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check center with cake tester (should come out almost clean).
Cool on rack for about an hour, then place in refrigerator for several hours.

title: raspberry sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Combine brown sugar and butter in a small bowl, mixing well.
Spread brown sugar mixture over sweet potatoes.
Top with raspberries and juice.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes, spooning raspberries and juice over potatoes occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet; drain.
Add next 8 ingredients. Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover, stir and bake 30 more minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Blend in the chocolate, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, using medium speed. Beat 5 minutes after each addition.
Put in pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, add whipped cream and top with shaved bitter chocolate or chopped nuts.
Serves 7.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Combine all ingredients and cut bell peppers in half.
Take out seeds and stuff mixture inside.
Cook until done at 350°.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet and sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: hedgehog cookies
directions: Cut the dates into small pieces.
Chop the nuts and combine all the ingredients.
Make the cookies into rolls about the size of a quarter and roll them in 1/2 cup of coconut.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine cake mix with butter and 3/4 cup evaporated milk. Mix.
Spread 1/2 of the batter in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and rest of evaporated milk.
Pour over baked mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts, chips and remaining cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: baked bean medley
directions: In
the
Ultra 21 (2-quart) casserole, combine the pork and beans
in
tomato sauce, red kidney beans, garbanzo beans and lima
beans; stir in the onion, molasses, mustard and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put
all ingredients in a kettle with a tight cover and bake for 5 hours at 275°.
Do not open.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Add bananas. Add flour slowly. Mix well. Add pecans last and mix. Makes two loaf pans. Bake at 350° until bread rises and is golden brown. Top will usually burst. Cook about 45 minutes.

title: covenant pie
directions: Cook macaroni, drain, heat milk, mix in bread, cheese, butter, add to macaroni and onion.
Add egg last.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: my homemade ice cream
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar and eggs well with fork.
Beat in Carnation milk, whipping cream and salt; add vanilla.
After blending fruit, add this.
Pour into electric ice cream mixer and fill 2/3 full with the quart of milk.
This takes about 40 to 45 minutes to freeze.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: best peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in pan for 13 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and Marshmallow Fluff.
Beat well; add 1 cup flour.
Beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan, 9 x 13-inches.
Cool.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Wilt cabbage in water over low heat.
Melt butter and add flour.
Blend well and add milk, salt and pepper.
Keep stirring until it thickens (keeping over heat).

title: potato and cheese bake-in-foil
directions: Slice potatoes in the center of a piece of heavy foil about 18 inches long.
Add onion.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Add milk or cream. Salt and pepper to taste.
Fold the foil to form a tight seam down the middle and at both ends.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in the oven or on coals if you're camping.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cake is done, immediately cover the top of cake with 1 (7 ounce) jar marshmallow cream.
Do not remove cake from pan.
Pour icing over marshmallows after cake cools.

title: french cherry delight
directions: Gradually beat sugar into beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Combine crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Fold into egg whites.
Mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool; add powdered sugar, vanilla and cream cheese to Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth and spread over baked egg white mixture.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: banana orange breakfast drink
directions: Peel and freeze banana overnight in airtight plastic bag. Slice banana into blender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Whirl until smooth.
Serves 2.

title: persimmon candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a bubbly boil on high heat, stirring all the while.
Reduce heat to medium and boil the mixture, without stirring, until a small amount forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Now, stir in persimmon pulp and nuts.
Let cool at room temperature for a while, then beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Spread candy on a cloth, wrung out in cold water.
Roll and let cool.
Remove the cloth; slice and serve.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli packages in microwave at High for 3 minutes or until package is flexible.
Layer
broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a medium bowl, mix soups, sour cream, lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Stir in chicken; pour over the broccoli.
Set aside.

title: creole mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve with cheese, crackers, chips or on sandwiches.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: orange bar cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend into egg mixture. Stir in nuts, coconut and candy orange slices.
Spread into a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm and roll in powdered sugar or sprinkle over the top.
They freeze nicely.

title: quickie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in a casserole and top with crushed (unsalted) potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: creamed cheese tarts(serves 12)
directions: You will need 12 muffin papers.

title: best chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix together chicken, soup and sour cream.
Put in large casserole dish.
Cover top with melted margarine and crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Mix the brownie mix as directions on package. While this is baking, cut all the marshmallows in half. As soon as brownies come out of oven, put marshmallows on cut side down. Then add icing of powdered sugar, cocoa, Crisco and just enough hot water to make fluffy. This icing is also good on any cake.

title: quick hungry man's lunch
directions: Cut up onion and in a two-quart skillet, add margarine and onion.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until onion is tender, then add Campbell's soup and Libby's roast beef (mashing up the roast before adding is best).
Cook on medium heat until contents begin to boil.
Add Tabasco to serving, if desired.
Serve with peanut butter and crackers or peanut butter sandwich.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll tenderloin in mix.
Place in covered roaster pan.
Put onion and mushrooms over tenderloin. Pour creamed soups plus 1 can of water over tenderloin.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: quick spinach quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Pour evenly into two unbaked pie crusts (9 or 10-inch).
Bake at 425° for 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into 6 slices each.
Serves 6 to 12.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Separate eggs and put whites in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Beat in yolks, one at a time, and let cool.
Stir in brandy.
Beat egg whites and fold into chocolate mixture.
Chill in fridge for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, beat heavy cream until stiff and add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Put on top of chocolate mousse and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and boil the potatoes until done.
Boil the eggs.
Crush the potatoes; put in the eggs and crush them.
Add the mustard and sausage spread, then the salt and pepper.
Add cut up onions.
Set the stove at medium, then serve hot or warm.

title: spinach spread
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Squeeze with paper towels and drain more as you mix all ingredients and chill.
Good with pumpernickel bread or rye (small loaves).

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornstarch.
Cook 1 cup water and cornstarch until transparent, stirring constantly.
While hot, pour over other ingredients, and beat until smooth.

title: odom's barbecue sauce
directions: Whisk together all ingredients until smooth.
Refrigerate for a few hours to blend flavors.
Pour over berries.

title: cheddar welcome wafers
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine cheese and butter using an electric mixer.
Add cayenne pepper, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and flour; mix completely.
Form dough into a log 20-inches long and 1-inch round.
Cut log in half and wrap each half in wax paper.
Refrigerate logs for at least 1 hour.

title: lemon salad with custard top
directions: Mix 2 packages lemon jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 2 cups warm 7-Up.
When almost jelled, add 1 (No. 2) can crushed pineapple, drained and 1 cup miniature marshmallows.
Refrigerate until set.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well.
Pour into a unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Set aside.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine mix, butter, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Stir by hand. Press 1/2 of mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chips over crust.
Pour caramel over, then pour rest of the mixture in.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: three bean pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, stir corn oil, vinegar, onion, red pepper, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper until blended.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture forms a doughy lump, pour out on table and knead.
Store in an airtight container.

title: crock-pot tamale supreme
directions: Mash hot tamales with a fork.
Mix with chili and cheese. In crock-pot, cook until all ingredients are thoroughly blended. Serve with king size Fritos.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch round layer pans.
Cool.
Freeze; then split layers.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
In a separate pan, mix soup, enchilada sauce, green chilies and milk.
Heat to steaming. Layer sauce, ground beef and tortillas in a casserole dish.
Add cheese and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: portabella mushrooms
directions: Saut mushrooms, shallots and garlic in butter and olive oil for 6 to 7 minutes. Add raspberry vinegar and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Stir until melted. Top with 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Arrange breast halves in a greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with sauerkraut.
Top with cheese. Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serves four.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add pizza sauce. Put into bottom of casserole pan.
Layer with pepperoni, green peppers and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with sour cream and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with crescent rolls and bake until the rolls are done.

title: pioneer beans
directions: Mix and bake slowly, approximately 2 to 3 hours at 300°.
Can also be made and cooked in a crock-pot, approximately 2 hours on high, then turn to low for 2 to 3 more hours.

title: ada's banana pie
directions: Boil unopened can of condensed milk in a saucepan of water for 3 hours over low heat.
(It won't burst.)
Cool in the refrigerator.
You can leave it for days at this point.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, then top with shredded cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: hop n john
directions: Place
ham hocks in 5 quart saucepot.
Add 8 cups water or enough to cover hocks.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce to low heat;
simmer 1 1/2 hours.	Remove bones, leaving meat in saucepot.
Add
onions,
celery,
salt,
pepper and peas; stir well.
Simmer slowly about 45 minutes or until peas are tender and liquid
level
is	low.
Stir
rice into peas.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Stir with fork to fluff rice mixture.
Serves 8.

title: aunt lou's best roast beef
directions: Rub oil all over roast.
Combine seasonings and rub over roast.
Bake at 350° to 425° for 20 minutes per pound.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring to a boil:
sugar and Karo.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour mixture over Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Melt together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over cookie.
Place in refrigerator for a few minutes to harden icing.

title: shellfish gumbo
directions: Cut off the stalk ends of okra; cut into 1/4-inch pieces and blanch in salted water.
Drain the water.
Heat the vegetable oil in a deep pan and add the chopped vegetables, okra and herbs.
Let stew about five minutes; add the shellfish and chicken stock. Cover and bring to a boil; simmer until clams and mussels open. Season with cayenne, lime juice, salt and pepper.
Serve with buttered steamed rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all of this well!!!

title: chocolate chip banana nut bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly butter and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces.
Spread in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion in large skillet, breaking up meat.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper. Spoon mixture over cabbage.
In small saucepan, heat soup and water to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Fluff with fork before serving.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute celery, onion, carrots and mushrooms until tender.
Add milk and broth and heat to boiling to thicken.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt margarine, stir in sugar, flour and milk. Pour into bottom of Pyrex dish. Pour sweetened peaches over and bake 1 hour at 345°.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Blend in blender and store for a long time in refrigerator. This is delicious spread over cream cheese and spread on crackers. Also good heated with small frankfurters.

title: jack's cookie stuff
directions: In a glass 8 1/2 x 11 x 2-inch dish, layer soaked until soggy chocolate chip cookies and soaked coconut macaroons.
Then apply layer of Cool Whip.
Keep layering until all ingredients are used. Apply layer of Cool Whip over top.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: stuffed cabbage(verze ripiene al forno)
directions: Remove core from cabbage and cover cabbage with boiling water. Let stand
minutes.
Remove as many cabbage leaves as possible (15).
Let
leaves
stay
in
boiling
water until filling is prepared.
In
frying
pan
heat
oil and add beef. Brown beef and chopped
onion.
Drain all grease from pan, and mix beef with
rice,
eggs,
salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese and 1/3 cup tomato sauce.
Mix well.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix meal, milk and eggs.
Stir in oil.
Add peppers, corn, onion and cheese.
Stir only enough to mix.
Pour batter into greased pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: frozen pea salad(24 hour)
directions: The day before serving, cover bottom of a 4-quart dish with layer of shredded lettuce.
Top with layer each of onion, celery, water chestnuts and thawed peas.
Spread with mayonnaise. Sprinkle with sugar, cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Top with bacon and tomatoes.

title: carrot nut bread
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Melt chips and milk in microwave for 2 minutes.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of the peanuts.
Pour mixture over peanuts.
Spread!
Top with remaining peanuts and press into mixture.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: mammaw's chocolate gravy
directions: Combine cocoa, salt, flour, and sugar; stir thoroughly.
Over heat, slowly add water.
stir until thickened.
Eat while hot over biscuits.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Melt margarine and add milk. Beat eggs and add sugar, flour and baking powder gradually. Then add vanilla and margarine/milk. Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 12 pan. Use Caramel Icing.

title: mexican stack-up
directions: First Layer:
Spread refried beans on platter.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased pan and bake for 45 minutes at 525°.

title: birthday party punch
directions: Have all ingredients cold.
Mix just before serving.
Children love this easy red punch.
Serves 25.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Pour off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a baking dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: southwestern corn
directions: Brown onion in fat (and bacon if you are using this).
Add ham pieces (after the onion is cooked), corn, milk and potatoes.
Cook over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes, until potatoes are cooked. Stir frequently to prevent burning.
Serves 6.

title: mini-bite mint cookies
directions: Place 1/2 (10) of peppermint candy into bag and crush.
Repeat with rest of candy (1/2 cup total).
Mix flour and soda; set aside.
Mix butter and sugar with mixer until blended.
Add flour mixture and beat until blended.
Stir in crushed candy.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes, then remove to rack. Yields 100 small cookies.
(Good for children to make.)

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, 1 1/4 hours. Serve with rice. Serves 6.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in flour and extracts.
Bake in a buttered and floured pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Use a 1 1/2 quart ring mold or a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: smores
directions: Build a fire.
Take 2 graham crackers and put chocolate piece on 1 cracker.
Roast marshmallow.
Put marshmallow between a graham cracker.
Smoosh and enjoy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain thoroughly.
Mash and add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly (around 30 to 40 minutes, depending on oven).
Serves 6 to 8 people.
tags: Stove Top corn bread stuffing mix

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple; drain oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar. Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
You can substitute vanilla yogurt for sour cream, if you wish.

title: microwave hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook
broccoli
in
box 5 minutes on full power.
Drain well. Melt
margarine
in a 2-quart casserole for 45 seconds. Saute chopped vegetables and mushrooms for 3 minutes.
Add the diced cheese and melt on 80% power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: elegant cream puffs
directions: Put water in pan, add butter.
Let come to a boil.
Add flour to boiling mixture.
Cook for a few minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and keep beating until it cools off enough to add eggs.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly each time. Grease cookie sheet and put heaping teaspoonful of batter 1 1/2 inches apart.
Put in 400° oven for 38 minutes.
Don't open oven door.
Cool on rack.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and strawberry jello and add 1 cup water. Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool and add strawberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll dough out on a cookie sheet.
Brush with melted garlic butter.
Sprinkle with cheese and pepperoni.
Roll to fit in greased bread pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Enjoy!

title: barbecups
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sauce, onion and sugar and mix well.
Press a biscuit into ungreased muffin cup, getting dough up edges of muffin cup.
Spoon beef mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Having chilled, mix all ingredients. Serves 12.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Spread a generous amount of peanut butter on each cracker. Place another cracker on top to make a sandwich.
Melt almond bark in microwave or in double boiler.
Almond bark should remain quite hot for the next step.

title: cherry cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar and mix well.
Add egg yolks and beat until smooth and light.
Add sour cream, vanilla, lemon juice, lemon and orange rind and blend thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into cream cheese mixture. Turn into spring-form pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.
Turn off heat and leave cake in oven 1 hour more.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice onto wax paper. Beat butter, sugar, honey and eggs in a large bowl and beat on high with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Sprinkle 1/4 cup of flour mixture over fruits and nuts. Add remaining flour mixture alternately with milk to the fluffy mixture, beating until smooth. Stir in nuts and fruits. Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched. Cool in pan on wire racks 20 minutes. Loosen around edges and middle with knife if needed.
Turn out on rack and cool completely. Wrap in foil or plastic. This cake slices better the next day.

title: red beans-n-rice
directions: In crock-pot, mix all ingredients.
Cook until done (all day on low).
Cook rice.
On plate, layer rice with bean mix on top.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; make into small balls.
Bake until done.
Put in colander to drain off excess oil.
Simmer in sauce.

title: texas cake
directions: Place flour, sugar, salt and soda in mixing bowl.
Put oleo, water and cocoa in pan and bring to a boil.
Pour this over the dry ingredients and mix well.
Add sour cream and eggs and mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Place apple slices in baking dish or pan.
Arrange bread strips over apples.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour or spoon over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Good reheated.

title: jane's baked beans
directions: Saute bell peppers, onion and celery.
Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cook in crock-pot overnight on low (8 to 10 hours).

title: bacon sourdough muffins
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve active dry yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in 2 cups of warm water, 2 cups all-purpose flour and 1 tablespoon of sugar or honey.
Beat until smooth.
Cover bowl with cheesecloth.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 to 10 days or until mixture has a fermented aroma, stirring 2 or 3 times a day.
(Fermentation time depends on room temperature.
A warmer room hastens fermentation.)

title: lemon dessert
directions: Put graham crackers on the bottom of a small square pan.
Pour mixture of first 3 ingredients over the crackers and put in the freezer until firm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add in order listed.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix together.
Grease 3 small loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: amandel koek
directions: Mix ingredients with hands.
Form ball and spread in a pie dish.
Smooth top to make it even.
Bake 60 minutes at 325°.
Check at 50 minutes for oven variance.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add food coloring to tint a pale green.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans, mixing well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
Store in loosely covered container. Best eaten within a day or two.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together.
Roll dough in the cinnamon and sugar.
Grease the bottom of a tube pan and sprinkle chopped pecan pieces into it.
Place the rolled balls around in the pan and let them sit overnight.
Next morning, mix together margarine and 1 cup light brown sugar.
Pour over the top of the balls and add more pecan pieces.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: potato cheese pie
directions: Butter a deep glass baking dish; coat with bread crumbs. Season mashed potatoes with butter and grated cheese.
Alternate potatoes and cheese.
Top with remaining bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake in medium oven until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Freezes well and microwaves well.

title: red chicken with almonds(pollo almendrado rojo)
directions: In a plastic or paper bag combine flour, 1 teaspoon of the salt, the thyme and pepper.
Add chicken pieces, a few at a time; shake to coat.
In 12-inch skillet, brown chicken pieces in hot oil about 15 minutes.
Add onion, paprika and garlic; cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, water and remaining 1 teaspoon salt.
Place toasted almonds in blender container; cover and blend until almonds are finely chopped.
Add to chicken. Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Toss bread crumbs and pineapple together and place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: three layer cake(with lemon cheese frosting)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Alternate flour, eggs and milk to mixture; mix well.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 floured and greased cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: guatemalan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 F. In a large bowl combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Stir in bananas, coconut milk, vanilla, and butter.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into a greased 5 x 9 inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour 15 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf, 16 slices.

title: chicken and shrimp egg rolls
directions: Cook cabbage in a frypan with butter.
Lay 1 egg roll pastry flat.
Crack eggs into separate dish.
Smooth edges of egg roll pastry with eggs.
In the center of egg roll pastry, layer cabbage, chicken and shrimp.
Roll like a burrito.
Cook in oven on bake at 375° in a Pam sprayed, flat pan.

title: fresh fruit trifle
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Chill.
Tear cake into bite-sized pieces.
In clear glass bowl or trifle bowl, arrange half the cake pieces.
Top with half the pudding, then half the fruit, ending with half the whipped topping.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Chill and serve. Serves 12.

title: easy honey-mustard chicken
directions: Cooking Time: Depending on type of chicken.
Servings: 4.

title: pineapple sugar-free pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spareribs with barbecue sauce
directions: Place ribs in a shallow pan; cook at 350° for 1/2 hour. Prepare sauce as follows:
chop the onion.
Cook in lite oil until clear (I use olive oil).
Combine with onion the vinegar, sugar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, water, celery and salt.
Simmer for 5 to 7 minutes until ingredients are well mixed. Baste all of sauces over ribs and reduce heat to 300°.
Keep basting several times for 1 hour.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice.
Brown ground beef and sausage together.
Salt and pepper.
Cut garlic clove and onion and chop bell pepper in with ground meat and sausage.
Drain meat.
Combine rice and meat in large casserole dish.
Add can of cream of mushroom and sprinkle Kitchen Bouquet to the darkness you want.
Mix well until all rice is brown in color.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Sift flour; cream butter and sugar.
Add flour.
Add lemon extract and 7-Up.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Use large tube pan.
Serves 12.

title: apple brownies
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart pan.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift the flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon; add to first mixture. Add the apples and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Double the recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy apple muffins
directions: Mash the apples slightly with a fork.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix by hand only until moistened (do not overbeat).
Fill muffin tins half full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Yields 1 to 1 1/2 dozen.

title: marinated fruit
directions: Mix fruit and liqueur and refrigerate several hours.
Serve over slices of pound cake.

title: layered southwestern salad
directions: Layer lettuce and next 7 ingredients in a 3-quart glass bowl. Serve immediately with vinaigrette dressing.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: cavatina
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese) in 9 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: In a bowl, combine eggs, muffin mix, cream-style corn and whole kernel corn, sour cream and butter or margarine.
Spread into an 11 x 7 inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 10-15 minutes more, or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% Bran and let stand.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add buttermilk, bran and boiling water; mix.
Add Bran Buds, then add dry ingredients.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 19 minutes or until brown on top.
Can add raisins with dry ingredients if desired.

title: shaker lemon pie(from the napa register)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk.
Bake until light brown, about 5 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine undrained pineapple and strawberry jello.
Heat and stir until jello is dissolved.
Cool about 15 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk.
Chill until mixture is thickened. Fold in whipped topping and walnuts.
Turn mixture in 8-cup mold, cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Unmold onto lettuce lined plate.
Garnish with fresh strawberries or sliced pineapple.

title: tortilla soup(4 servings)
directions: Cut tortillas in 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Fry tortillas in a small amount of oil until brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels. Heat 2 teaspoons vegetable oil.
Add onion; saute until translucent.
Add green chilies, broth, chicken, salt to taste and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in lime juice.
To serve, pour into soup bowls and add tortilla strips.
Float a lime slice in the center of each bowl.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saturate and fry chicken in oil.
Mix the remaining ingredients together except rice and paprika.
Pour over chicken and saturate. Add rice and paprika last.
Bake 60 minutes at 325°.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and carrot fine.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Let set overnight.
This will keep for a long time.

title: sauteed frog legs provencale
directions: Cover frog legs with water; soak for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain on paper towel.
With mortar and pestle, grind a few corns of allspice and 1/2 teaspoon basil.
Season flour with small amount of salt, coarse ground black pepper to taste and paprika.
Dip legs in milk; coat with flour mixture.
