Cook frog legs in hot oil with small amount of chopped garlic until golden brown, turning to cook on both sides, 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain.

title: strawberry pound cake trifle
directions: Prepare pudding according to package and add the sour cream.

title: mint julep cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine bourbon, lime juice and creme de menthe. Stir in lemon-lime soda.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with mint.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop the potatoes, carrots, celery and onion into small pieces. Cook potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper in two cups of water until done.
Add creamed corn.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Peel and cube raw potatoes.
Line a casserole dish with raw potatoes.
Cover with browned meat and onions.
Pour soup and mixed vegetables on meat; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1 tablespoon mix per cup of boiling water.
Store remaining mix in airtight container.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese. Add Cool Whip. Spread on cake half. Put on top and the rest of the cake. Put cherries on top of and some in the middle of the cake. The cake cuts best with electric knife.

title: date rolls
directions: Cook dates, sugar and margarine until thickens. Add nuts and Rice Krispies. Cool. Roll into balls and then in powdered sugar.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add green pepper, onion and 1 cup celery; saute.
Combine soup mix and boiling water in large saucepan.
Stir in rice and cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add sausage and salt.
Stir well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining celery on top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 20 minutes.

title: 4-day make-ahead cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs, water and oil.
Bake in 2 round pans. Cool; slice into 4 layers.
Between each layer, put filling.

title: microwave cocktail wieners
directions: Cut wieners in 3/4-inch pieces; set aside.
Combine sauce, sugar and seasoning in a 1 1/2-quart casserole or serving bowl.
I heat sauce and wieners separately in microwave until both are heated thoroughly, then combine.
Makes approximately 1 quart.
I always double recipe.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix broth, lemon juice, basil, thyme and pepper in a non-metallic dish.
Add chicken.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or more. Broil on rack 6 inches from heat, turning and basting with marinade.
Serves 4.

title: lemon glazed cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place flour, salt, shortening, nutmeg, granulated sugar and orange rind in bowl.
Add egg yolks and butter.
Incorporate well with pastry blender.
Add cream and pinch dough to incorporate.
Roll on floured surface until about 1/4-inch thick.
Dust with more flour, if needed.
Using assorted cookie cutters, cut shapes and place on buttered cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes.

title: holiday bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread nuts in the bottom of the pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over nuts.
Arrange 1/4 pound candied cherries and 1/4 pound candied pineapple over batter.
Press slightly into batter. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion; drain well. Put in casserole dish. Add margarine, whipped egg and soup; mix well. Add cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in salted water until done.
Drain and toss oil, vinegar, salt and pepper. Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine. Sprinkle over beans and cook. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon curd squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Press in an 8 x 9-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine the next ingredients together and pour over baked crust.
Bake until light brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: blueberry pretzel dessert
directions: Combine pretzels and sugar; stir in butter.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Top with pie filling.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes or until serving.

title: texas fudge
directions: Drain jalapenos, seed, stem and chop well.
Combine with cheese.
Sprinkle mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour beaten eggs over the cheese and pepper mixture and bake 25 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Cool slightly and cut into squares to serve.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well. Beat in egg yolks 1 at a time. Mix all dry ingredients together. Add oil, potatoes, pecans and hot water. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add to mixture and
put in three 9-inch round baking pans. Bake at 350° until cake is done.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place beer (still sealed) in a bowl of hot water in an upright position.
In a mixing bowl, place flour, sugar and eggs; add beer all at once.
Stir just enough to mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake for about 1 hour.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake(this recipe is 50 years old)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: burritos
directions: Brown meat.
Add chili powder, flour, garlic, salt and pepper, sauces and onion.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Layer beans in middle of tortilla.
Layer meat sauce.
Layer shredded cheese.
Fold over sides and wrap with foil.
Heat in a 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.
Can freeze.

title: easy summer salad
directions: Cook pineapple for 2 minutes.
Add gelatin and cook 2 minutes longer.
Set aside to cool.
Prepare whipped topping according to directions.
Add cottage cheese and stir well.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold or shallow dish and chill until firm. Serves 8.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Slice eggplant into 1/2-inch slices. Dip into
egg
mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until brown
on
both
sides and soft in the middle.
Drain on paper towel.
Dilute
tomato
sauce with a little water.
Put thin layer
in greased casserole dish.
Layer sauce, eggplant and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat until finished.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle
with
Parmesan
and top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake
at
uncovered,
for
45 minutes or until heated through.

title: creme cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix together. Fill in center of cakes. Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Cool and add fruit or fruit pie filling, if desired, about 1 teaspoon on each.

title: baked pork chops, creole style
directions: Rub a deep skillet or casserole with oil.
Arrange potatoes in bottom.
Arrange chops over them.
Spread chops with onions, bell peppers and tomatoes.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and thyme.
Put bay leaf and parsley on top.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chops are tender.
Discard bay leaf and serve.

title: american chop suey
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken wings
directions: Grate onion, ginger and garlic to suit your taste.
Soak wings in mixture for 20 minutes or more and deep fry in vegetable oil at 350° to 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown ground round in shortening in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook, covered, over high heat until steaming; remove from heat.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Split English muffins and place on baking sheet. Dice the green pepper. Combine all ingredients and spread on the English muffins. Cut into quarters and bake for 15 minutes.

title: ham cheese rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend mustard, butter, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on both sides of split rolls.
Add ham and cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Heat for 10 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix sifted flour, sugar, shortening, salt and orange juice. Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in baking powder.
Add eggs, water and orange rind.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 nine-inch layer cake pans which have been rubbed with shortening.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: glorified cheese cauliflower
directions: Prepare and cook cauliflower until tender.
Pour Cheese Sauce over hot cauliflower.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: tacos
directions: Place onion and garlic in a 1-quart ovenware casserole.
Cook for 5 minutes or until onion is soft, stirring occasionally.
Add salad oil, tomato sauce, water, jalapenos, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt and cumin to onion and garlic.
Cover and continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Place beef and 1 cup onion in 1 1/2-quart ovenware casserole.
Cover.
Continue cooking 6 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup chili sauce.
Heat tortillas 15 minutes.

title: perfect chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour three 9-inch round cake pans.
Combine the cocoa with boiling water, stirring until smooth. Cool completely.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
In a large bowl, beat together the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the cocoa mixture to the creamed mix.
Do not over mix.
Blend just enough to moisten the dry ingredients.
Pour the batter into the pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes and remove and cool completely.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream peanut butter and oleo.
Gradually add sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually add to cream mixture.
Roll into balls, then in sugar.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven; press Hershey Kiss in center.
Bake 2 minutes longer.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Bring juice to boil.
Mix sugar, flour, beaten eggs and 1 cup water.
Place on stove.
Stir in boiling pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Pour over pineapple chunks. When cool, add marshmallows.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all except nuts in top of double boiler, stirring until smooth. Add nuts and mix. Spread quickly in buttered pan. Cool.
Do not put in refrigerator until completely cool.
Cut in squares.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve over salad greens.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut semi-frozen steak into 1/8-inch strips with the grain of the meat.
Mix all seasonings and sauces in a bowl.
Place the meat strips in glass dish and pour marinade over that.
Let marinate overnight in glass dish.

title: mardi gras cake
directions: Melt together butterscotch morsels and water.
Cool.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add butterscotch mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Blend well. Divide into two 9-inch pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Turn onto cake rack.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter on medium heat together.
Add vanilla and 10x sugar when melted.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat while stirring.
Put in pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut after cooling.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl and then form into a ball.
Serve with any flavor.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir beef in 2 tablespoons butter in 10-inch skillet over low heat until brown. Reserve 1/2 cup bouillon. Stir remaining bouillon, garlic and salt into skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and onion. Cover and simmer until onion is tender (5 minutes).
Shake reserved bouillon and flour and stir gradually into beef mixture.
Stir and boil 1 minute. Stir in sour cream. Heat through.
Do not boil. Serve over hot cooked noodles or rice. Yields 6 servings.

title: summer iced coffee
directions: Combine coffee, cinnamon and cloves in a 1-quart measurer. Add boiling water.
Stir until coffee mixture is dissolved.
Add cold water.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.

title: sausage casserole
directions: In rectangle shape dish, break 2 slices of bread.
And half of sausage and half of cheese.
Repeat:
2 slices of bread (broken) and rest of sausage and cheese.
Pour over top the 6 eggs, beaten with salt and pepper, dry mustard and the milk. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mincemeat cookies(favorite recipes of jefferson's country)
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Beat egg and blend with butter mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Stir into egg mixture, blending thoroughly.
Fold mincemeat into mixture.
Drop by teaspoon and bake in hot oven at 400° about 8 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown chicken in oil, stirring occasionally.
Add water, wine, broccoli and soup.
Bring to a full boil, separating broccoli pieces.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seacoast salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Add additional mayonnaise before serving, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and gelatin; add remaining ingredients except vanilla and nuts.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball stage. Add vanilla and cool for 15 minutes.
Beat for 7 minutes or until firm.
Add nuts; pour into buttered pan. Cool; cut into squares.

title: fourth of july cake
directions: You will need 4 to 6 small sparklers and safety matches.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix vegetables and 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight.
Next day drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices and simmer 10 minutes. Add to vegetables.
Cook approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Chow will change to a dull green color.
Pack and seal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar. Add eggs. Coat nuts in dry ingredients. Add to oil and sugar mixture. Slowly add carrots and pineapple. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick simple bean salad
directions: Heat beans until hot.
Drain well.
Grate cheese; put over hot beans.
Crush Fritos.
Stir in the beans and melted cheese.
Serve while hot.
Hint:
Kids love this.

title: spicy snaps
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Mix dry ingredients and mix well with buttered mixture.
Roll balls and put in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta fagiola
directions: It is important that you use a rather heavy pot in which to cook pasta faciola.
Cover the bottom of the pot with about 3/4 of an inch of olive oil.
Cut celery and onions into small pieces. Slowly saute them in the oil.
Add the can of mushrooms; continue to saute the mixture.
Add a lot of pepper.
Add the 4 cans of stewed tomatoes.
Continue to simmer 1 hour over low heat.

title: noodle bake(easy lasagna)
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer. Cook egg noodles and drain; add softened cream cheese and container of sour cream.
Layer in casserole dish, noodle, meat and both cheeses; repeat.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: sugar batons
directions: Into a large bowl, measure flour, butter, vanilla, egg and 1/2 cup sugar.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well blended, occasionally scraping bowl with spatula.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon half of dough into decorating bag with medium rosette tube.
Pipe dough into 3-inch lengths, about 1-inch apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cookies lightly with sugar. Bake 6 to 8 minutes until golden.
Carefully remove cookies to racks to cool.
Repeat until all dough is used.
Store in tightly covered container to use up within 1 week.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Dip sliced bread in mix and fry in butter in a skillet until brown on both sides.

title: shrimp chip dip
directions: Cut shrimp into very small pieces and mix well with the remaining ingredients.
Use as a dip or spread for potato chips or crackers.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt well.
Add milk slowly. Cook over low heat until bubbly and thick.
Add vanilla after pudding is cooked.
Put in bowl.
Put plastic film over pudding.

title: acorn squash
directions: Halve squash.
Place in baking dish. Grate carrot into fine strips. Saute carrot in butter and honey.
Put sauteed carrots in center of squash - add a pat of butter and 1 tsp. honey. Bake 350° until tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine cheese, soup, sour cream, onion and 1/4 cup butter. Turn into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until casserole is golden brown and potatoes are tender.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In blender, mince onions and jalapeno peppers with half of the corn.
In a bowl, mix cornmeal, eggs and remaining corn.
Then add sour cream, oil and cheese.

title: fresh mushroom cutlets
directions: Divide	mixture
into
8 portions and form each portion into a patty
inch
thick.
Press
each
patty between 2 sheets of waxed
paper.
In
a
skillet melt butter.	Fry the patties on both sides until crisp on the outside and moist on the inside. Serve with shoyu.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chalupa
directions: Cover with water; cook until meat falls apart.
Take out bone and fat; shred and cook until thick.
Serve with corn chips, lettuce, tomatoes, green chilies, cheese, avocados, black olives and salsa garnishes and tortillas.

title: bran waffles
directions: Combine all dry ingredients/nuts.
With fork, beat egg yolks and brown sugar together until crumbly and yellow colored.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks stage.

title: husband's cake
directions: Measure Crisco and sugar into mixing bowl; blend together. Combine tomato soup with water and soda; add to Crisco mixture alternately with all sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans together and pour in pan for crust. Cook and cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip and pour over crust.
Mix pudding according to directions on box. Pour over cream cheese mix.
Add layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then liquid and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Very moist cake.
No need to frost.

title: linguini in clam sauce
directions: Saut first 7 ingredients for a few minutes.
Grate Romano cheese.
Boil linguini and drain.
Mix all ingredients together, adding Romano cheese last.	Serve with additional Romano cheese.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg. Spread in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. In a large bowl, mix together pumpkin, 4 eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg, sugars and evaporated milk. Mix with mixer until well blended. Pour over "crust". Top with walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham crackers.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat egg, margarine and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Cover with drained pineapple.
Then sliced bananas, then cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook mixture 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef.
Add ground beef. Cook on low heat 1 hour; serve on buns.

title: guiltless french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, mash ripe banana to creamy consistency. Add cinnamon and salt and mix well.
Slowly add milk and beat with fork until banana is completely liquified.

title: shrimp delight dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Mold into ball or any shape you want.
Chill until ready to serve. Serve with cocktail sauce and crackers.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel egg and cut in half longways.
Remove yolks and put into a mixing bowl.
Combine yolk and mayonnaise to a thick yet smooth consistency.
Add one teaspoon of mustard and mix.
Add one teaspoon of pickle juice and mix.
Spoon mixture back into egg white.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pork chops with honey mustard sauce
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in bag.
Add chops to bag; shake to coat.
Shake off excess flour.
Reserve flour mixture. Heat oil in medium skillet over medium heat.
Add chops; cooking until golden, about 8 minutes.
Set aside.
Save 1 teaspoon fat, discard the rest.
Wipe skillet clean, return fat, adding red peppers and carrots, cooking until soft.
Add flour mixture until browned.
Stir in last 3 ingredients, cooking until thickened. Add pork chops and juices, simmer, covered, 4 minutes or until chops are cooked through.
Serve with sauce.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cocoa, salt, vanilla and milk.
Place in 2-quart microwave bowl.
Place butter on top and cook, uncovered, 2 minutes on Medium-high.
Remove from oven and stir until blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into baking dish.
Chill 30 minutes in freezer.
Cut into small squares.

title: glazed baked ham
directions: Remove wrappings from ham, but do not remove rind.
Place fat side up on rack in shallow uncovered baking pan.
Bake at 300° for length of time as follows:

title: dry roux
directions: Use
1 deep iron pot;
add
flour
(all-purpose).
Heat oven to 400°, stir once in a while.
When roux is light brown, remove from oven and stir until it is cool.

title: blueberry breeze
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with graham crackers.
Make pudding as directed.
Pour over crackers.
Pour blueberries over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 sugar and vanilla.
Work flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm or colored sugar before baking.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the eggs.
Beat 4 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Bake in two layer pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: shaker recipe for boiled fruit cake
directions: Put the sugar, water, shortening, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves on to boil at a slow simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
When cool, stir in 1 beaten egg, 2 scant cups of flour and the baking soda with a dash of salt.
Add the fruit and nuts.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Be sure to test the cake as fruit will make it soft in places and if taken out before done, it will settle and fall.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown meat, squash and onions together with salt and pepper. Drain off juice.
Put in layers meat, cheese and oleo.
Pour in milk.
Place in 350° oven until cheese is melted; brown if desired.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients until meat is done. Drain. Cook instant rice. Fold rice into meat mixture. Add Kitchen Bouquet, salt and peppers. Add green onions last. Serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 425° until a knife inserted into side of filling comes out clean.
The center may still look soft but will set up later.

title: sauerkraut dumplings
directions: Cook meat until tender; pour sauerkraut into broth and meat. Cook for 15 minutes.
Make dumplings; roll out, cut and drop into boiling broth.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until dumplings are done.
You may use a little more water for drop dumplings.

title: dried fruit balls
directions: In a chopping bowl or food processor, finely chop the apricots, dates, raisins and coconut.
Stir in the sugar and juice, mixing the ingredients thoroughly.
Snip off enough mixture to shape into 1-inch balls (first dusting hands with powdered sugar).
Roll the fruit balls in the coconut or nuts.
Place the fruit balls in layers in a container, separating the layer with wax paper and tightly cover the container.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and melted butter.
Dissolve soda in prune juice.
Sift flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and baking powder together.
Add prune juice and prunes to egg mixture.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Bake in layers (9-inch pans) at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: beef with peppers
directions: Heat pan; add oil and garlic.
When garlic turns brown, remove.
Add beef and brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add consomme and continue to cook until meat is tender.
Add mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Cook until sauce thickens. Add green peppers, sliced lengthwise and ginger.
Heat and serve with rice.

title: cape cod oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in egg, sugar, molasses and milk.
Melt together butter, shortening, oatmeal, raisins, and nuts.
Blend well and arrange on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes until edges are browned.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, butter and 2/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Take half of mixture and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt caramels in remaining milk over medium heat.

title: lemon bread
directions: Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Have ready the juice of one lemon and 1/4 cup sugar; mix well.
Pour over loaf when taken from oven and let juice soak in.

title: cheesy macaroni
directions: Cook elbow macaroni; rinse.
Melt butter and add flour and dry mustard over low heat.
Makes thick tan colored paste.
Add milk. Allow to heat.
Gradually add grated cheese and stir over medium heat.
Add white pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook in oven at 250° until top is brown.
Sprinkle paprika over top.

title: hacienda hamburger
directions: Cut olives
in
small
pieces.
Heat
oil and add meat. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in onions and celery. Cook
about
minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly
and cook until mixture is boiling.
Put into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and drain well.
Brown ground meat and drain.
Add onion rings.
Let sit.
Mix beans, catsup and molasses.
Combine all and place in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt annease's yeast rolls
directions: Warm large bowl.
Pour in warm water and yeast.
Dissolve. Add egg, sugar, salt and margarine.
Mix with electric mixer. Gradually add 4 cups of flour, then mix by hand to add last 2 cups of flour.
(Can add up to 1/2 cup more, if needed.)
Spread a little melted margarine on top.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours to rise, then punch down.
Make rolls and put on greased baking sheet.
Top with margarine.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In mixer, combine sugar and spices and stir until mixed thoroughly.
Add pumpkin and stir until mixed, then beaten eggs. Add evaporated milk and milk and mix thoroughly and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: red devil balls
directions: Blend together cream cheese and deviled ham.
Refrigerate until easy to handle and shape into small balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate again until ready to serve.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix
squash,
onions,
pepper,	mustard seed and celery seed together
and
let stand for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with salt. Mix sugar and vinegar together, bring to a boil.
Add pickling spice. Add
squash
mixture.
Boil
until pepper changes to a dull green. Put
into jars while hot.	Seal and turn jar over on the top. Let stand for 24 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine
all
ingredients. Bake at 375° for 1 hour in a loaf pan. Delicious!

title: hamburger barley vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer until barley is cooked and vegetables are tender.
Serve with cornbread, if desired.

title: gourmet ole burgers
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, taco spices and ketchup; blend well.
Shape into patties.
Grill or broil burgers 5 to 7 minutes on each side or to desired doneness.
Top each burger with a slice of cheese.
Return to heat until cheese melts.
Top with salsa, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nut crunch candy
directions: Mix together and boil until a little over hard crack stage (about 325°).
Pour into buttered 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool. When cool enough, refrigerate.

title: cauliflower slaw
directions: Combine mayo, milk, lemon juice, dill weed, salt and pepper. Mix shredded cauliflower and radishes and toss with dressing. Refrigerate.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Dissolve soda in milk.
Add sugar and margarine.
Cook over high flame until forms soft ball in water.
Cook in a large container.
Beat until creamy and spread.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain.
Peel and cut the potatoes in half lengthwise slices.
Place, cut side up, in a greased, shallow baking pan.
Set aside.

title: yorkshire pudding(over 50 years old)
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and continue beating.
Add sifted flour with salt and beat until smooth.
Put hot drippings from roast beef into 9-inch pie pan.
Heat until smoke is rising from pan; pour in batter.

title: heath bar ice cream pie
directions: Let each layer freeze for one hour.

title: jules' chicken tortilla soup
directions: Put broth, corn, Ro-Tel and tomato sauce in large stock pan. Add chicken, onion and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until ready to eat.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese, crumbled tortilla chips and chives.

title: reeses peanut butter cups
directions: Mix peanut butter and oleo together.
Then add sugar. Form into balls, chill 1 hour. Dip balls into chocolate mix and let air dry.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well; add vanilla and milk.
Sift in dry ingredients and blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 10 medium pies.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Sprinkle onion soup on bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan, then pour 1 can soup, 1 can water, 1 can soup, 1 can water then rice.
Lay salted chicken on top.
Bake, covered, 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: beer cheese soup(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until soft, but not brown. Add flour and mix well; let cool.
Bring chicken stock and beer to a boil and add to the mixture while stirring constantly.
(Never add 2 hots together, always 1 hot and 1 cool so they will blend.) Bring back to a boil and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add in eggs, oil, vanilla, pecans and apples. Mix well, but do not beat. Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°. Cool in pan before removing.

title: northwood's buttermilk cake or rice-paddy bundt cake
directions: Stir powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Add enough milk or brandy to make of drizzling consistency.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend well.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.

title: layered salad
directions: Salad can be prepared and stored in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: wild rice salad with raisins
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Add all ingredients.
Toss together. Serve at room temperature.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: aunt lee's pie crust
directions: Whip Crisco and water with fork until fluffy.
Cut in flour with fork.
Pastry will be extremely tender, so handle with care. Bake as per pie recipe.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, soda water and flour together well.
Add mayonnaise and vanilla.
Stir together thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan or a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: jiffy apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
For a moister recipe, use a smaller casserole dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nuts over apples. Sprinkle cake mix over all.
Melt margarine.
Mix with milk. Pour evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.
Great with vanilla ice cream.
This can also be made with cherry pie filling.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add flour and milk alternately, having added salt and baking powder to flour.
Add flavoring last. Use tube pan which has been greased and floured. Bake at 150° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Half bread and spread with butter.
Lightly sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cover with cheese.
Add a light topping of honey. Bake until brown and cheese melts.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Blend in condensed milk. Slowly add lime juice and salt and mix well.
Add cream of
tartar to egg
whites
and
beat
until
foamy.
Continue beating, adding sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time until egg whites peak.
Fold 6 tablespoons of the meringue into the pie filling mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell or graham cracker shell.
Top with remaining
meringue
and
bake
until
golden brown at 425°. Cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together to use as a dip for assorted fresh fruits. May also be used as a filling for crepes.

title: jumbo cornburger
directions: Combine first six ingredients and mix thoroughly. Spread half of the mixture in 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round casserole or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except tomato and cheese.
Spoon over meat.
Cover with remaining meat mixture. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Last 5 minutes, arrange tomato on top; sprinkle with cheese.

title: talerina
directions: Cook ground beef with onions; add seasonings.
Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Combine meat and noodles, then add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Add cheese and let melt.
Serve hot.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook together first four ingredients to hard ball stage (260°).
Add peanuts and continue cooking until golden brown (300°).
Stir to keep from burning.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Add soda quickly until it foams.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet.
Let it get cold, then break into pieces.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Stir together sugar, starch and Kool-Aid.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Return to heat just to thicken.
You can either use as a topping for ice cream or pour over 1 or 2 quarts of fresh or frozen strawberries.

title: salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir.
Chill and serve.

title: lemon mystery pudding
directions: Place in casserole dish which is set in a pan of water and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: wrapped chicken breasts
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cut chicken breasts in half lengthwise.
Remove the bones, if desired.
Set aside. Arrange sliced beef over the bottom of the baking dish. Wrap each chicken breast in 1 slice bacon with ends under the breasts. Arrange over sliced beef.
In a medium saucepan, combine milk, White Sauce Butter Balls and bouillon granules.
Use a wire whisk to crush the butter balls. Stir constantly over medium heat until slightly thickened and smooth. Remove from the heat.
Preheat oven to 300° (150° C). Stir parsley, mushrooms and sour cream into white sauce.
Pour over chicken breasts. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours in a preheated oven until it is golden brown and tender.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook and stir celery in butter until tender.
Stir in croutons, cheese and salt.
Cut thin slice from stem end of the green peppers.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and outside.
Place each pepper on piece of double thickness heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Fill peppers with cheese stuffing (above).
Wrap securely in foil.
Cook directly on medium coals for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once, or on grill 3 to 4 inches from hot coals for 30 to 40 minutes, turning once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ella davis' chocolate snappers
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and egg.
Add syrup and chocolate. Sift dry ingredients and add to first 3 ingredients.
Shape into balls using a tablespoon measure.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let stand for a minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: chicken casserole with stove top stuffing
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix chicken, milk and soup together.
Place in casserole.
Make stuffing according to directions on package.
Pour over top of the casserole mix.
Pour reserved chicken broth over the top for added moisture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more. Serves 8.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt oleo; mix with milk and cocoa.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Frost while cake is warm.

title: oven tacos
directions: Brown meat, onion, garlic and pepper in skillet; drain.
Add taco seasoning and refried beans; heat through.
In separate bowl, combine mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and water.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with small amount of sauce mixture.

title: soy sauce pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Let marinate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Remove and cook (broil, roast or charcoal).
Pour remaining sauce over cooked pork chops.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Combine. Layer with Doritos. Top with Cheddar cheese. Cook 30 minutes.

title: fry stir-fry
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Whip egg and add to chicken.
Stir constantly until cooked.
Add in vegetables and soy sauce.
Stir constantly.
Add in ginger, sesame and water chestnuts.
Stir. Serve over rice.
Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6, depending on actual quantity of rice and vegetables.

title: basic fritter batter for deep fat frying
directions: Put eggs in small mixing bowl and beat for 1 minute.
Add milk, flour, baking powder, salt and shortening.
Fry clams, scallops, crabs or your choice of seafood in fat for 2 to 3 minutes at 400°.

title: honey apple ribs
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except ribs.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbling.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes, then cool.
Boil ribs 45 minutes.
Place ribs in baking dish.
Pour cooled sauce over ribs.
Chill several hours.
Bake or grill.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Place oil in an 8 inch oven proof skillet, tilt to coat bottom and sides. Place in 425° oven for 10 minutes. In a bowl, combine cornmeal mix, flour and baking soda. Beat egg and buttermilk together, add to dry ingredients just until moistened. Pour into hot skillet. Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon lush
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix margarine, nuts and flour with hands like pie dough.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and pat down lightly.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat to a boil.
Put in Jell-O mold or bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 cup berries in saucepan; add water, bring to boil, simmer for 3 minutes.
Strain juice from cooked berries (discard berries).
Add water to juice to make 1 cup if needed.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan; slowly stir in the berry juice. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, cook 3 minutes.
(A few drops of red food coloring may be added, if desired).
Cool slightly; while cooling, arrange remaining (3 cups) sliced or quartered berries into pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries and chill.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: pork chop 'n potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops, sprinkle with season salt; set aside. Combine soup, milk, sour cream and 1/2 teaspoon season salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put pork chops on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes (covered).
Add cheese and onions and put back in oven uncovered for 5 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onions in a large skillet until beef is cooked and onions are tender.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Spoon a little beef mixture over bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of tortillas and chili, ending with tortillas.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in double boiler over hot water.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Stir well and then drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Also good without peanuts.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with wheat thins.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix well all ingredients except the last two.
Refrigerate until well chilled. Roll in small balls.
Place a toothpick in each ball. Chill again until firm.
Melt over hot water the last 2 ingredients.
Dip each ball in this mixture and chill until firm.

title: tomatoes and okra
directions: Wash pods.
Cut off stems.
Cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling salted water for 10 to 15 minutes or until almost tender; drain.
Cook onion and green peppers in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in sugar, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add tomatoes.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Add cooked okra; heat through.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp-seashell macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish top with paprika and place sliced black olives around base of salad.
Keep refrigerated when not using.

title: chicken with okra
directions: Sprinkle okra with lemon juice; set aside. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. In nonstick skillet, brown chicken on all sides. Remove to plate. Add onion flakes and bouillon to skillet; let stand 5 minutes. Add water, tomatoes, okra with lemon juice and chicken. Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked throughout.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center, reserving pulp.
Chop eggs and celery.
Mince green onions.

title: roast chicken and vegetables
directions: Brown bacon until crisp in a large frying pan. Remove bacon and pour off fat.
In bacon drippings, saute potatoes, onions and carrots until lightly browned.
In a large casserole, place chicken. Add browned vegetables and crumbled bacon.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. After 45 minutes, remove the cover and let chicken brown, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: onion meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, onion soup mix, milk and egg; mix well.
Press mixture firmly into an ungreased loaf pan.
Loosen edges with a spatula and invert molded meat loaf onto an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: world's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine sugars, butter and cream with sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, mix together.
In a separate bowl, sift the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Mix well. The dough should be stiff.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Line cookie sheets with baking parchment or wax paper. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool on wire racks. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin dessert squares
directions: Mix cake
mix,	egg
and
melted
butter.
Pat	into
a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together pumpkin mix, 2 eggs and milk.
Pour over top of cake mixture.
Mix remaining cake mix, brown sugar,
cinnamon,
butter
and
nuts	until
crumbly and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked apples(microwave)
directions: Place apples in 2-quart glass baking dish.
Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon butter in center of each apple. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with sweet or sour cream.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Cut fish into 1-inch chunks.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, add water, clam juice and potatoes. Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add fish, clams, half and half, evaporated milk, scallops, shrimp and Old Bay.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until fish is opaque.

title: green chicken enchiladas(enchiladas verdes)
directions: Heat the Tomatillo Sauce in a small, covered pan over low heat. Warm the chicken in a separate pan over low heat.
Sprinkle chicken with a little water so it won't dry out.
Stir in the sour cream, onion and salt. Set aside off the heat, covered.

title: gelatin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Prepare cake according to package directions. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan. After baking, let cool in pan 15 minutes. Pierce cake at 1/2-inch intervals with a large fork.

title: chocolate drop candy(child's recipe)
directions: Put 1-quart saucepan on range burner and add sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Stir to blend.
Turn range burner to medium heat.
Continue stirring and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove saucepan from heat and quickly stir in vanilla extract, oatmeal and peanut butter, making sure ingredients are well-blended, working quickly.
Drop mixture onto waxed paper by the teaspoon.
Cool 15 minutes.
When completely cooled, store in an airtight container.

title: cabbage slaw that keeps
directions: Put cabbage and onion in plastic bowl.
Put all other ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and onion.
Shake well.
Refrigerate.
Take out and shake at least twice a day.
Keeps at least 10 days.

title: sweet potato scallop
directions: Pare and boil sweet potatoes; mash them. Add brown sugar, 1 cup miniature marshmallows and seasoning salt; dot with oleo or butter. Core, pare and slice apples. Top with sliced apples and 1/4 cup miniature marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or when apples are done.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease and flour 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan. Beat eggs at high speed until thick; gradually add 1 cup sugar and beat 5 minutes. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice. In separate bowl, combine flour and next 5 ingredients; gradually stir into pumpkin mixture. Spread batter evenly in pan and sprinkle with 1 cup pecans. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cook diced eggplant in some water until fork-tender.
Drain water.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter or oleo until nearly done.
Add 3 more tablespoons of the butter.
Add cracker crumbs and mix well.

title: german style baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute onion in two tablespoons of bacon drippings. Combine onion with other ingredients and put into casserole dish.
Crumble bacon on top. Bake 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in large skillet.
Cut up garlic and onion real fine.
Cook and stir until slightly brown.
Stir in tomato juice.
Blend in chili seasoning.
Salt to taste.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add jalapeno peppers to make hot chili.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add carrots and oil.
Stir well.
Add eggs, pecans and raisins and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in two cake pans.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crumble first package of taco shells (or 1/2 bag of tortilla chips) and spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown ground beef with taco seasoning and spread over top shell layer.
Next, sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over meat.
Spread sour cream over Cheddar cheese.
Next, place the 6 slices of American cheese. Top with remaining crushed shells or chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peppers provencale *
directions: In heavy skillet, heat oil and butter until butter is melted. Add onion and peppers.
Season with herbes de Provence and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, stirring frequently, about 45 minutes or until vegetables are limp and lightly browned, marmalade-like.
Add garlic and basil and cook 5 more minutes. Remove from skillet; let cool and remove excess oil.
Serve with toast points at room temperature or as a quiche filling.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Put 1/2 of bread in greased casserole.
Cover with 1/2 the cheese, then alternate, ending with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Let stand covered in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan, cook pudding and milk until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Meanwhile, in bowl, cut peanut butter in confectioners sugar until crumbs form.
Set aside 2 teaspoons of crumbs.
Sprinkle the rest into pie shell.
Pour pudding over crumbs.
Chill until set.
Top with whipped cream. Sprinkle crumbs on top.

title: fresh berry ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine ingredients; mix well. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: beef casserole(ching delight)
directions: Brown beef in frypan until crumbly.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole pan.
Arrange thawed peas over meat.
Cover with sliced celery.
Mix soup, cream, salt, pepper and onion and pour over the celery.
Sprinkle chips over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: fehn's macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar. Blend in saltines, nuts, dates, flavoring and baking soda.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream as a topping.

title: banana nut bread(low-fat)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter (melted).
Add eggs and pecans. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Brown crumbled beef and onion together in two 9-inch pie pans in a 425° oven.
Stir occasionally.
Spread cooked macaroni over meat mixture.
Pour on 1 1/2 cans of tomato sauce and water. Sprinkle on seasonings and toss all together lightly. Top with cheese and choice of toppings.
Pour on remaining tomato sauce. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan, over medium heat, cook the onion in butter until tender (about 8-10 minutes).
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended smooth.
Pour the milk in 1/4 cup increments, allowing the mix to wholly absorb the milk before adding the next 1/4 cup.
Continue adding milk until you are comfortable with the thickness, and beware of allowing it to become too thin!

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix well, except for bacon; place bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add all ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until pudding is set.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, salt and 1 pint of milk, then add second pint of milk.
Add bread pieces, pecans and raisins to the liquid.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put a pan of water in the oven under the pudding while baking.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
When done, top with small marshmallows and return to oven for about 10 minutes or until the marshmallows have melted and are brown.

title: spaghetti with pesto
directions: In blender or food processor, combine basil, spinach, cheese, nuts, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Blend with several on-off turns until a paste forms, stopping the machine several times and scraping sides.
With the machine running slowly, gradually add the oil and 2 tablespoons of water and blend to the consistency of soft butter.
Toss with hot cooked pasta.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: bacon crackers
directions: Cut bacon pieces in half.
Wrap around crackers.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be made ahead of time and reheated.
Drain well.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Mash cranberry sauce and fold in pineapple and nuts; mix well into gelatin.
Oil salad mold and fill.
Refrigerate until well set.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, celery, onion, salt, pepper, lemon juice and mayo. Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle chips on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly and hot through. Makes about 6 servings.

title: beef stew and dumplings
directions: Cook and stir beef in oil in Dutch oven until beef is brown. Add 3 cups hot water, 1/2 tsp. salt and the pepper. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Stir in carrots, potatoes, pepper, celery, onion, 1 tsp. salt and the bay leaf. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaf.
Prepare dumplings.
Shake 1/2 cup cold water and flour in covered container.
Gradually stir into stew; heat to boiling stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; reduce heat.

title: red's pepper relish
directions: Layer pepper with salt in a glass bowl.
Allow to stand at room temperature, stirring several times, 3 hours.
Drain peppers well to remove all liquid.
Mix drained peppers, tomatoes and onions in a large pot.
Stir in sugar and vinegar.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth and crack with a hammer.
Place in pot.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Remove spice bag.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine chopped vegetables.
Tie spices in a bag and add to vegetables.
Cook rapidly, stirring often to prevent sticking. When the vegetables have cooked down to about half the original amount, add the sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil rapidly for 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Pour into hot jars.
Wipe rims.
Place lids and rings on tightly.
Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Start processing time as soon as water returns to a boil.

title: raised sweet dough
directions: Add 3 cups flour to first 5 ingredients and dry yeast.
Mix and let stand for 15 minutes.
Next, work in rest of flour.
Let this stand for 2 hours.
After they are in pans, rest the dough again for 1/2 hour.
Bake bread 45 minutes to an hour in a 350° oven; bake rolls 20 minutes.
Doughnuts can also be made of this dough.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix in mustard.
Pour over bread in greased casserole.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour on egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in pan of hot water.
Can be made and refrigerated night before.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup oats and 6 tablespoons margarine on low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of the crumbs.
Combine egg with remaining crumbs and press in prepared pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: garlic sour cream dressing
directions: Mix in blender until well blended.
May be thinned with a few tablespoons of milk if desired. Serve over vegetable salad. Do not store for over 48 hours.

title: filled cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients except preserves.
Chill dough overnight. Roll out dough.
Cut into rounds and place 1 teaspoon preserves or your favorite jelly in middle of round.
Cover with another cookie round and press edges together.
Slit top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: orange jello
directions: Heat pineapple juice in saucepan.
Then dissolve Jell-O in heated pineapple juice.
Dissolve Cool Whip in pineapple juice and Jell-O.
Mix in buttermilk.
Mix in pineapple.
Refrigerate several hours.
Enjoy!
Yummy!
Good!
Kids love it.
Very easy recipe.

title: grilled doughnut desserts
directions: Cut doughnuts and marshmallows horizontally in half. (Use shears dipped in water to cut marshmallows.)
Place doughnuts, cut side down, on cooking surface of grill 5 to 6-inches from medium coals.
Place marshmallows, cut sides down, over holes in doughnuts. Cover and grill 2 to 3 minutes or until doughnuts are golden brown.
Immediately push chocolate kisses point side down, into marshmallows.

title: irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9-inch round loaf pan.
Put the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Work in the shortening with a pastry blender, then quickly stir in milk.
Add the raisins and caraway seed, stirring just enough to distribute them evenly.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead about 20 times.
Put the dough in the pan and bake for 20 to 30 minutes. Cut into wedges and serve.

title: chicken olen
directions: Cut cooked chicken in small pieces. Mix all ingredients, except cheese and tortillas. Add 1/2 of cheese. Pour chicken broth in casserole. Layer tortillas and chicken mix. Top with rest of cheese. Top with foil. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on greens and garnish. Makes 8 servings.

title: maids of honor
directions: Make up pie crust per directions.
Cut in circles with a glass and fit into muffin tins.
Put in a spoon of strawberry jam.
Make up Jiffy cake mix per directions.
Put 2 tablespoons in each cup cake tin over the strawberry jam.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans right away.
Frost with a plain butter frosting and add a small piece of cherry for garnish.
This is an English pastry.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Stir ingredients together in order listed.
Refrigerate dough for 12 hours.
(Dough may be kept several days in fridge.)
Roll dough into favorite shape on lightly floured board and let stand and rise for 2 hours.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: italian red rice and sausage
directions: Boil sausage in water for 15 minutes.
Drain sausage, pouring broth into measuring cup.
Add tomato juice from canned tomatoes to make 4 cups of liquid.
(Add water if necessary.)
Pour mixture back into pot.
Add rice.
Add crushed tomatoes, then add spices. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: lime party salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in top of a double boiler.
Pour hot mixture over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese and stir until cheese dissolves.
Add pineapple and let cool.
Blend in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Chill in a 9x12-inch pan until firm. 12 servings.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: george and harold's candy
directions: Mix and boil 4 minutes, the margarine, sugar and milk on medium heat.
Take off heat and quickly add vanilla, cocoa, Marshmallow Creme and crunchy peanut butter.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients well.
Pour in middle of peaches.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven until brown.

title: grandma's salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly in medium bowl.
Stir in sugar, butter, flour and pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes.
Pour into greased, 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: fire and velvet zinger
directions: In a large skillet, brown the sausage, onion and pepper.
Add tomatoes, uncooked macaroni, sour cream, milk, sugar, salt and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until the macaroni is tender. It should still be a little saucy and soupy. Serves 4.

title: brown sugar and cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, buttermilk powder, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cream sugar, shortening and egg together.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients.
Blend in the water until the batter is mixed thoroughly but not overbeaten. Blend topping ingredients until crumbly.
Put paper liners in 12 muffin cups and fill with batter.
Sprinkle topping evenly over muffins.
Bake for about 25 minutes.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except coriander.
Cover and refrigerate, if desired.
Stir in coriander just before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil about 9 to 12 lasagna noodles until tender, stirring occasionally so they don't stick to kettle.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients in bowl.
Let stand a few minutes. Pour over crackers, stirring the oil and herbs (dill weed settles to bottom).
Mix well with spatula.
Divide between two jelly roll pans.
Cook in a 200° to 225° oven for about an hour (stir at 30 minutes and switch top and bottom pans).
Turn off oven.
Let cool in oven overnight, as this makes them crisp.
Store in an airtight container.

title: yule tide yams
directions: Boil fresh yams until tender and peel or drain well if using canned yams.
Mash yams and add the next six ingredients.
After mixing them together thoroughly, place in a buttered 2-quart casserole and top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops.
Boil potatoes until soft; add to pork chops. Cook carrots until almost done, add to meat and potatoes.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Season with salt, pepper and onion.

title: tea cookies
directions: In a bowl, blend together the butter and the powdered sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Blend together the flour, salt and baking powder (note: just a dash).
Add flour mixture to butter mixture, blending well.
Add the chopped nuts.
Combine well.

title: crunchy banana
directions: Crumble or crush flake cereal.
Stir in wheat, if desired. Spread peanut butter on banana chunks. Roll in cereal and eat.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, salad oil, sugar and pumpkin well.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and spices and blend well.
Add flour and blend well.
Pour into a 12 x 18-inch jelly roll pan with 1-inch edge. (Pan should be greased and floured.) Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange cloud
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cinnamon. Combine water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice. Measure 1 2/3 cups gelatin.
Fold in orange sections.
Spoon into serving bowl and chill until set, but not firm.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; add onion and chili powder.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes, soups, water, salt, pepper, oregano, bay leaves, hot peppers and butter.
Cook on low heat for about 25 minutes.
Place in warm crock-pot.
Cook 10 to 12 hours.

title: mexican beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Boil in same water next morning with salt and butter.
Reduce to simmer.
Cover and cook about 2 hours or until tender.
Cut bacon into 1/4-inch pieces. Fry partially.
Add to beans.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: mountain muffins
directions: Grease 1 dozen cup muffin pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pans and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In baking pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over butter.
Pour milk over crumbs.
Top with chocolate and peanut butter chips.
Press firmly in pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Put pie filling in 10-inch pie plate. Cover with nuts. Cover with cake mix and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugars, shortening, eggs and molasses until light and fluffy.
Stir flour, salt, spices, soda and baking powder together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk until well mixed.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat to boiling the sugar, corn syrup, salt and water stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stir in peanuts or nuts of choice. Set candy thermometer in place and continue cooking, stirring frequently until temperature reaches 300°.
Remove from heat, immediately stir in butter and soda; pour onto cookie sheet and spread.
Cool; break into pieces with hands.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in greased pan 35 to 40 minutes at 375°. Does better if you bake it thin rather than thick.
Great served with Broccoli-Cheese Potato Soup.

title: venison meat
directions: Spray roaster pan with Pam.
Slice meat 1/4-inch thick and place one layer in the roaster.
Cut the onion and green pepper and lay on top of meat in roaster.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Roll meat slices in the flour mixture and place on top of the first layer of meat in the roaster.
Add more onion and pepper. Add tomato juice in between the layers.
Place the rest of the flour mixture and remaining ingredients on the top layer.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: blueberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold blueberry yogurt into whipped topping.
Fold blueberries into yogurt mixture.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 3 hours.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook beef and onion until slightly browned.
Add water and potato, bring to boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
To serve, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: fast yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients. Knead dough about 25 times on floured board.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and cover.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican hominy skillet
directions: In skillet brown beef; drain off fat.
Stir in hominy, green pepper, water, chili seasoning and onion soup mix.
Cook and stir until heated through, about 5 minutes.

title: egg cheese strata
directions: Mix well and pour over bread and cheese.
Soak several hours or overnight, covered with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour covered.
Remove foil and bake 1/2 hour longer.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: nut balls
directions: Melt butter.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well and make into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler or heavy pan.
Dip balls and place on wax paper.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix cake mix and dry yeast.
Combine with salt, egg, warm water and 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour.
Mix to make a soft dough. Knead; let rise 1 hour in a warm place.
Punch down.
Make into rolls.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush with melted oleo.
Let rise 2 or 3 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes a dozen or so rolls.

title: butter chews
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Mix thoroughly with flour.
Pat mixture into a greased 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes until light brown.
Cool.

title: lillie's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion. Drain. Mix all ingredients well. Pour into a round casserole dish with lid. Cook at 350° in oven for 45 minutes.

title: skillet zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini about 1/4-inch thick (do not peel).
In large frying pan, saute garlic in oil for about 3 minutes.
Add zucchini; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in a mixture of parsley, oregano, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes more, or until tender.

title: low-cal new england dinner
directions: Put all items in baking dish.
Place one tablespoon flour over items.
Cover with water.
Cook in conventional oven or crock-pot.
Season to taste.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground beef and onion lightly.
Combine tomato paste with water, sugar, salt and pepper, mixing until smooth.
Add to meat mixture.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes; add noodles and cook until tender, stir occasionally.
Serve with grated cheese over it.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix all together and fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in an angel food cake pan greased and floured.

title: super taco
directions: Cover a 12-inch round serving plate with a layer of bean dip. Layer will be thin.

title: punch bowl salad
directions: Bake cake, cool and crumble.
Begin layering in punch bowl, 1/2 the cake, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 whipped cream, 1/2 nuts and 1/2 coconut.
Put in all of the cherry pie filling.
Repeat layering in the same order, beginning with cake and ending with nuts and coconut.
Serves 20.

title: lace oatmeal cookies
directions: Add all ingredients to beaten egg.
Drop by small teaspoon on aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not remove from foil until cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine, butter and shortening.
Add eggs (one at a time), beating well.
Sift and measure flour and baking powder.
Add milk after adding part of flour.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: my baked apples
directions: In a flat dish, layer thick layer of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with apple pie spice.
Pour or spoon over this a generous amount of honey (depending on tartness of apples).
Repeat these layers for remaining apples.
Top with pats of butter on top.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Arrange crescent dough triangles in a 12-inch pizza pan with points toward middle of pan.
Spread triangles out to form a crust.
Beat egg and brush
over dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix and spread over cooled crust.
Top with remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: coconut sour cream frosting
directions: Mix together and put on cooled cake layers.

title: no egg icebox pie
directions: Mix milk and thawed lemonade.
Add half of the Cool Whip. Stir good.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top.
Chill.

title: taco bean soup
directions: Brown meat, onion soup, taco seasoning and onion.
Put in large pan and add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a simmer.
Drain juice off beans and add to mixture.
Drain corn and add.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
(Can use any kind of beans desired.)
Good with corn bread.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone.
Cook onions.
Mix chicken and mushroom soups and broth.
In casserole, put layer of dressing and layer soup mixture over it (with chicken and onions).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix the potatoes per directions or use leftover mashed potatoes. Mix ground beef, green beans and tomato soup in a large baking dish.
Place mashed potatoes in ring around top of mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: russian tea
directions: Add 2 1/2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Add extract sugar or sugar substitute if not sweet enough for your taste.
Good on a cold day or any day.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes into quarter-inch slices.
Discard the ends.
Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper.
In a bowl, combine the flour and meal.
Dredge the tomato slices in the flour and meal mixture, covering each thoroughly.
Heat the oil in a heavy frying pan, preferably well seasoned cast-iron.
When the oil is hot but not smoking, fry for about 3 or 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: praline pie
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar and pecans together.
Pat into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° until shell is brown and praline mixture is bubbly.
Cool.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices onto waxed paper.
Beat brown sugar, shortening and egg with applesauce.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake about 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Sift powdered sugar over top before serving.

title: texas millionaire pie
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and melted oleo.
Pack into pie pan to make a crust, then freeze.
Spoon in vanilla ice cream.
Store in freezer.
Combine milk, butter, sugar, chocolate and vanilla in saucepan; cook over low heat until sauce is smooth, stirring frequently.
Let cool.
Serve pie topped with sauce, whipped cream and slivered almonds.

title: cabbage wedges with sauce
directions: Cut cabbage in 8 wedges.
Cook in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine mayonnaise and milk in a small pan; stir until smooth.
Add vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat; stir until hot.
Pour over cabbage; sprinkle with paprika.

title: mom's cheese ball
directions: Mix well with hands.
Roll in pecans.
Chill and serve with crackers.
This is wonderful for a party.

title: california slaw
directions: Layer shredded lettuce, onions (shaved very fine), grated carrots, chopped celery and cooked peas in salad bowl.
Top with small dabs of mayonnaise or Miracle Whip and sprinkle with a teaspoon of sugar.
Repeat for desired quantity.
Over top layer, sprinkle crisp, crinkled bacon.
Do not toss.

title: italiano marinara
directions: In saucepan, heat oil and saute onion and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid and spices.
Simmer until the tomatoes break up, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green beans
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° just to heat through.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine and put in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until hot.

title: linguini salad
directions: Boil linguini and drain. Cold wash and drain. Toss in serving bowl with the Italian dressing.
Sprinkle with the Salad Supreme to taste. Add the tomato and cucumber before serving.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard, pepper and vinegar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cook two minutes and remove from heat.
Stir in corn, green pepper, pimento and onion.
Pour into a pint jar, cover tightly and refrigerate for several days before serving.
Makes 1 pint.

title: potato kugel
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in greased pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 1 hour or until light brown.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Stew chicken until tender; remove from the bones.
Cook stew meat until tender.
Mix all ingredients together, broth and all. Simmer for an hour.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix together butter, Crisco, sugar, and eggs.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls and cover with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes and immediately remove from baking sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Spread tuna in bottom of baking dish. Add onion and peas (including juice). Spread soup over. Add cheese. Cover with potato chips. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: wassail
directions: Bring cider to boil; add sugar and stir until dissolved. Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Reheat.
Serve topped with nutmeg.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook all ingredients except spices and shrimp in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup of water and let cook down for 30 minutes. Add shrimp seasoned well with Creole seasoning.
Add parsley, bay leaves, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Serve over cooked rice.

title: steak subs
directions: Cook meat until very tender, reserving liquid.
Cool meat and shred.
Add meat juice, onion and gravy mix to meat.
Cook until gravy thickens.
Line bun with meat, lettuce, tomato and cheese. Enjoy!!

title: easy pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brush egg yolk on pie crust. Bake for 5 minutes; set aside. Combine the cheese, sugar and eggs in a large mixing bowl and beat on medium speed until smooth. Add spices and pumpkin; continue mixing until well blended. Spoon mixture into pie crust and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set. Let cool; refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Serve plain with
a dollop of whipped cream or scoop of ice cream. Serves 12.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onions and fry in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Boil until thick on simmer.
Put into jars and seal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Make ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: sugarless fruitcake
directions: Bring dates, raisins, prunes, margarine and water to a boil in saucepan.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Combine with flour, eggs, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and pecans in a bowl and mix well. Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Store well wrapped in refrigerator or freezer. Yields 24 servings.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Fry hamburg and onion together.
Drain.
In casserole, put hamburg and onion.
Put beans on top.
Put on the soup and then the mashed potatoes on soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: jelly balls(thumbprints)
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Work butter until creamy in bowl.
Add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and extracts; beat well.
Add flour gradually; mix until smooth. Shape level tablespoonfuls of dough into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets; press each ball with thumb.
Drop a little jam in each depression.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool on racks.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Beat until creamy the cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Put cookies in bottom of small paper cups in cupcake pan (paper work great).
Top with 1 teaspoon cheese mixture, then top with 1 teaspoon fruit pie filling.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: melon and grape salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put mixture in large glass bowl and refrigerate for two hours.
Serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and pat dry.
Remove and chop stems.
Set mushroom caps aside.
Heat butter over slow to medium heat and cook mushroom stems, onions and next four ingredients until onion is tender.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Place, stuffed side up, on broiling sheet and broil until mushrooms are tender, about 8 minutes.

title: chocolate dream bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, oatmeal, salt, flour and baking soda.
Cut in butter and put half of mixture into prepared pan.

title: polish lasagne
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Skillet brown hamburger;
stir in tomato
sauce
and	remove from heat.
Combine cheese, sour cream and onion.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges and bake as directed on the box; cool.
Mix together the crushed pineapple, instant vanilla pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Frost cake with this mixture and sprinkle top with chopped nuts and shredded coconut.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in 1-quart water.
Add all other liquids and chill.
Pour over sherbet and ginger ale.
Makes 45 servings.

title: cashew cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
In another bowl, sift next 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mix.
