Stir until a soft dough forms.
Fold in nuts. Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Yield: 5 dozen cookies.

title: hobo gumbo
directions: Fry, drain and break bacon into bite sized pieces.
Cut potatoes into niblits; cook until lightly brown.
Add eggs, salt and pepper to potatoes.
Scramble mixture and add bacon.
Cook until eggs are done.
Serve with toast.

title: orange ginger chicken
directions: Blend and combine all ingredients except chicken into a glaze. Baste continually with glaze while grilling chicken, or bake on rack in pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with orange curls, if desired.

title: cucumber sandwich
directions: Cut cucumber lengthwise.
Put mayonnaise on two slices of rye bread.
Place on cucumber slices, sprouts and tomato slices. Serves 1.

title: science hill inn biscuit pudding with bourbon sauce
directions: Break biscuits into small pieces in large bowl.
Add milk; soak 5 minutes.
Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla and add to mixture.
Pour melted butter into 2-quart casserole.
Add pudding and bake until set at 350° (about one hour).
Serve warm with Bourbon Sauce.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix all ingredients.
Fold in egg whites; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve with candy canes, cinnamon stick, orange slice or lime slice.
Cut recipe in half for blender. Recipe makes 1 gallon.
Dilute 1/2 cup egg nog and 1/2 cup milk.

title: cheese-vegetable lasagna
directions: Press spinach between paper towels and set aside.
Heat oil over medium heat.
Add broccoli, carrots, onions and garlic; saute 7 minutes.
Place flour in saucepan.
Add milk, stirring until blended.
Bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add spinach. Reserve 1/2 cup and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Swiss cheese.
Spread 1/2 cup spinach mixture in bottom of coated 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with noodles, then 1/2 of cottage cheese, then 1/2 of vegetables and 1/2 of spinach mix. Repeat.
End with noodles and top with 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Cover and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel cookie crisp
directions: Layer bottom of square dish with 20 caramels.
Flatten with spoon.
Heat in microwave oven until melted.
Break up half of the Oreo cookies and layer on top of caramel layer.
Repeat process with the remaining caramels and Oreos.
Cover with peanut butter layer.
Heat for 10 to 15 seconds and let cool before cutting.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo and flour.
Press on bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
In small bowl, mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust to edge.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Let stand 5 minutes and spread over cheese mixture.
Spread lemon layer with thin layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Can be frozen.
Defrost 2 hours.
Also, can be made with graham cracker crust.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, salt, milk and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to boil; cover and cook for 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook, without stirring, until a little of the mixture forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until mixture thickens and loses its gloss.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: meme's coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions; flour and grease bottom of pan only.
Remove from oven and punch holes in cake with fork all over and close together.
Pour Eagle Brand milk while cake is still hot, spread with spatula and let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over top of cake (thick).
Sprinkle coconut over top and press lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together sugars and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in creamed mixture. Stir in oats, candy and coconut.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks until foamy and the color of lemon.
Add butter, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour gradually and combine thoroughly.

title: neapolitan cookies
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set the mixture aside.
In a medium mixing bowl, beat margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat just until combined.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with waxed paper to hang over the sides of the pan.
Set aside.
Divide dough into 3 portions.
To one portion, stir in almond extract and red food coloring.
Pat into pan.
Next layer, stir in chopped nuts; pat evenly over pink dough.
To remaining dough, stir in melted chocolate.
Pat evenly over dough.
Chill 4 hours.
Lift the waxed paper and remove dough from pan.
Cut down center lengthwise, then slice each half 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350°for 12 minutes 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Transfer to a wire rack to cool.
Makes 72 to 84 cookies.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats, boiling water and soda; let stand for 20 minutes. Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well. Add oats mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool and frost with following frosting.

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: Combine sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir well. Sift into large bowl.
Mix shortening in with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Store in closed container. Does not need to be refrigerated.
Yield: 13 cups of mix.

title: fruit cocktail eggnog pie
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in eggnog.
Warm over low heat until gelatine is dissolved.
Chill until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Fold in whipped cream, flavorings and 1 1/2 cups fruit cocktail.
Chill again about 10 minutes until mixture mounds.
Put in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Decorate with remaining fruit cocktail.
Chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk together until forms a soft boil. Take off heat; stir in rest of ingredients. Stir until thick. Pour in pans.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 2 skillets of corn bread.
Bake as you regularly bake corn bread.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry chopped onion, garlic, parsley and celery leaves until onions are a good golden brown.
Add tomato paste and continue cooking 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent sticking and make a roux.
Add water and tomato juice and stir until completely blended.
Add salt, sugar and pepper and continue cooking for 1/2 hour.

title: sky high hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and egg.
Add 3 cups of flour and work into sugar and yeast mixture.
Add oil and 3 cups more flour.
Turn onto floured board and knead, adding flour as needed to make rubbery consistency.
Place in large bowl and cover with towel.
Let raise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch dough down and take small amounts and roll in balls.
Place in greased baking dish.
Brush oil on tops and let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 375° until tops are lightly golden.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Fry hamburg with onion.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup.
Add sour cream and corn with liquid.
You can rinse out cans with milk to thin a little.
Mix with cooked noodles and bake for about 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain off
fat.	Mix
cream
cheese with meat while it is still hot.
Stir
in
soup.
Pour into casserole dish and top with frozen
Tater	Tots.
Top
with
grated cheese.
Bake at 325° until hot and bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix and poppy seed.
In a small bowl combine eggs, water and oil.
Mix and add to dry mixture.
Beat 5 minutes at high speed.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 30 minutes.
Invert pan onto plate and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: tofu lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in the olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: cashew casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle some noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Also good with bamboo shoots, mushrooms, bean sprouts and diced mock chicken.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line a 12-inch pizza pan with foil; grease.
Press cookie dough onto foil.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Remove foil.
Place cookie crust on serving plate.

title: easy spaghetti bake
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain. In a large skillet, brown meat; pour off excess fat.
Add onion, spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir in cooked spaghetti.
Pour into a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover, bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes. Uncover; top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry fantasy salad
directions: Mix
together
Cool
Whip
and condensed milk.
Chill 1 hour. Add coconut, pecans, pineapple, marshmallows and cherry pie filling.
Stir together and chill overnight.

title: okie enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
(Salt & pepper to taste.)
In a separate pan add soup, water and chilies.
Heat until hot.
If soup is too thick you can add more water but don't make it too thin. Drain grease from beef mixture.
Fill tortillas with beef mixture and some cheese.
Roll and set in 9 X 13 baking pan.
(Coat bottom lightly with oil to keep enchiladas from sticking.)
Pour soup sauce over enchiladas to coat and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350 for about 20 minutes or until everything is heated through. 8 - 10 servings.

title: caramel crunch
directions: Melt butter and syrup in skillet.
Blend in brown sugar and cook 2 minutes.
Add cereal and stir until coated.
Spread on aluminum foil to cool.
Separate to eat.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add to mixture.
Chill one hour. Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Decorate to own taste!

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into cakes and fry until golden brown.

title: snow on the mountain
directions: Cook and cut up skinless, boneless chicken.
While chicken is cooking, chop tomatoes, green onions and celery into bite-size pieces.
Grate cheese.
Warm gravy.
Build your mountain in this order:
rice, Chinese noodles, chicken, gravy, tomatoes, celery, green onions, cheese, almonds, more gravy and coconut (snow). Serves 4, maybe more.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will also need 1 punch bowl.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Boil macaroni by directions on package.
Mix everything else and combine with macaroni.
Place in baking dish and bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.
(Add tuna if you desire.)

title: mom's friend barb's famous kugel
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Put noodles back in pot.
Use 2 tablespoons of butter to grease large rectangular baking dish.
Put the rest of the butter in the pan with the noodles.

title: beef cabbage soup
directions: Combine all and simmer.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: In large bowl, combine bar ingredients.
Stir by hand until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan or 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook diced zucchini in water 15 minutes or until tender.
Put carrots and onions with zucchini in colander to drain.
Melt oleo and add 1/2 packet spices out of stove top stuffing to the dressing.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreo cookies fine.
Blend soft cream cheese with 10x sugar until smooth.
Beat pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk and refrigerate (in separate bowl).
Add Cool Whip to cream cheese. Mix and blend until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Layer mix and Oreo cookies to serve in glass bowl.

title: party potato wedgies
directions: Scrub baking potatoes.
Cut in quarters lengthwise.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with garlic salt or seasoned salt.
Bake in a 375° oven until done.
Slit each wedge halfway through and stuff with grated cheese or crumbled bacon, etc.
Put wedges back in oven until cheese melts.
Serve warm with sour cream or sour cream and chives.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut uncooked chicken into small pieces, mix chicken, mushrooms and soup together (do not dilute the soup).
Place mixture into a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Cover with the shredded cheese and pour the wine over cheese.
Sprinkle dry stuffing mix on top and pour on melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered, until chicken is done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick; cool.
Add 1 1/2 quarts of strawberries. Put in baked pie shell.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Preheat oven at 300°.
Cook for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Slowly add milk to eggs
which
have
been beaten well. Stir in other ingredients and
pour into a buttered casserole. Set casserole in shallow pan of
water
and
bake
at 325° for about an hour.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown.
Cool; mix remaining ingredients and spread on dough.
Top with small cut (raw) vegetables:
broccoli, grated carrots, cauliflower, black olives, green peppers, etc.
Cut and serve cold.

title: chocolate chip cookies(makes 8 dozen)
directions: Mix sugar, oil, shortening, eggs, vanilla, salt and soda.
Sift cream of tartar into flour and add one cup at a time to the first. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Drain cherries, save juice.
Mix cherry juice and salad dressing and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Mix in all other ingredients together and pour dressing over them just before serving.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Sift all together until well mixed.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 tablespoons for 6 ounce cup of hot water. Yields 6 1/2 cups.

title: date pudding
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar like meringue.
Add dates.
Mix flour, baking powder and pinch of salt to egg white mixture.
Pour into cake pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: ham and egg breakfast sandwiches
directions: Spread each muffin half with deviled ham, using about 1/4 can for each.
Lightly beat together eggs, milk, salt, pepper and green onion.
Melt butter in frying pan; scramble eggs until done to stage desired.
Arrange eggs over each muffin half.
Top each with a slice of tomato and a slice of cheese.
Broil to melt cheese.
Serve at once.

title: rosemary bread
directions: Shape dough into round flat pieces.
Brush tops with olive oil.
Sprinkle first with fresh rosemary, then black pepper and last with garlic powder.
Let rise and then bake at 350° until done.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Let cool and peel.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Combine and mix ingredients.
Put into baking dish or 9-inch pie plate.
Pour heavy cream over potatoes and butter mixture.
Let stand about 20 minutes.
Bake at 175° until cheese is melted.

title: savory stuffed manicotti shells
directions: Brown the beef and drain off the fat. Combine Sloppy Joe seasoning, tomato paste and water. Stir half the sauce into the meat. Cook 8 Manicotti shells as package directs, pour enough sauce into a shallow baking dish to cover the bottom. Fill shells with meat and put into the baking dish.
Top with sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350°f. 180°c.
gas mark 4 for 25 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions.
Mix together mayonnaise, buttermilk and lemon juice. Toss broccoli and cauliflower with mayonnaise mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mounds
directions: Boil potato.
Drain water well and add margarine; mash well. While still hot, add powdered sugar.
Mix well and add coconut. Shape into balls (works better if you wet your hands frequently). Place on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
In double boiler melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: oatmeal carmilitos
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then mix with melted butter. Press 1/2 of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle boxed crust with chocolate chips, chopped nuts and ice cream topping.
Sprinkle the rest of the crumb mixture over this.
Return to oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before cutting.

title: pasta salad dressing
directions: Mix and toss with any favorite pasta-based salad.
Lo-cal. Delicious.

title: sweet-n-sour meatballs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Add water to juice if needed to measure 1 cup; pour into a large skillet. Add 1/3 c. water, vinegar, soy sauce, brown sugar and cornstarch; stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple, meatballs and green pepper. Simmer, uncovered for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over hot rice.
Yields: 6 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put into a Tupperware dish.
Cover; let stand overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, thoroughly.
Beat the 3 egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture and mix well.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake slowly for 1 hour at 300°.

title: cheese log
directions: Blend together all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into 6-inch log.
Coat with pecans and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix molasses, sugar and oil.
Sift flour with spices.
Add eggs and beat, then add flour mixture.
Mix soda with boiling water and when dissolved, add to mixture immediately.
Bake in 350° oven in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 40 minutes.
Serve with a vanilla sauce.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix almonds and cracker crumbs (be sure amount equals 2 cups). Add
remaining
ingredients
and
mix
well.
Place in well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and light brown.

title: brown rice
directions: Put rice in medium size casserole.
Pour beef bouillon and beef consomme directly on rice.
Cut pieces of butter over entire top of rice mixture.
Cover and cook on 350° for 45 minutes or until rice has absorbed the liquid.

title: cheese and garlic biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Just before removing from oven, brush with melted butter or margarine. Makes 12 biscuits, depending on size.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef and taco seasoning according to package directions; drain fat.
Put beef in refrigerator to cool; drain beans.
Add beans and cheese to beef.
Chill until ready to serve.
Add lettuce, chips, dressing, onion and tomatoes.

title: jane's mushroom pate
directions: Saute mushrooms in melted butter until all liquid is absorbed (approximately 5 minutes).
Put remaining ingredients plus mushrooms in food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Put in decorative mold and chill.
Serve on Wheat Thins.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook syrup, sugar, cream of tartar and vinegar to a soft boil stage.
Add butter, baking soda, vanilla and color.
Stir rapidly until very foamy.
Pour over popcorn; form into balls (with buttered hands).

title: granny's rice pudding
directions: Wipe a pudding dish with butter or spread.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour, then at 300° until rice is done.

title: chicken and broccoli braid
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine chicken, broccoli, bell pepper, garlic, cheese, mayonnaise, dill, salt, almond and onion.
Unroll crescent rolls onto a baking sheet; lay horizontally.
Press the perforations in the dough to create a solid sheet.
Arrange mixture horizontally down center of dough. Using a knife, cut vertical lines every 3-inches from the center (strips should remain attached to center).
Lift right and left strips opposite one another to make a braid; twist once and pinch together.
Brush with egg white.
Bake 25 to 28 minutes until golden brown.

title: spoon corn bread
directions: Melt butter in 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 baking dish.
Mix muffin mix with creamed corn.
Add slightly beaten eggs and sugar.
Blend with spoon.
Then stir in butter and sour cream.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken & broccoli braid
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Chop chicken and broccoli.
Place in a 2-quart bowl.
Chop bell pepper and add to chicken and broccoli.
Add garlic and cheese to vegetable mixture, mix gently. Add mayonnaise, dill mix, and salt; mix well.
Unroll 1 package of crescent dough; do not separate.
Arrange longest sides of dough across width of 12 x 15-inch rectangle dish.
Repeat with remaining package of dough.
Using pizza roller, roll dough to seal perforations.
On longest sides of baking dish, cut dough into strips 1 1/2-inches apart, 3 inches deep (there will be 6 inches in the center for the filling).
Spread filling evenly over middle of dough.
To braid, Lift strips of dough across mixture to meet in center, twisting each strip one turn.
Continue alternating strips to form a braid.
Tuck ends under to seal at end of braid.
Brush egg white over dough.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 25 to 28 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Cut and serve.

title: vickie's crunch pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into long strips.
Soak in mixture of lime and 1 gallon water overnight.
Rinse in cold water twice; spread on towel to dry.
Put pickling spices into mixture of sugar and vinegar, to cover cucumbers.
Bring to a boil; boil 30 minutes. Put into jars.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 50 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: pepper and tomato chicken
directions: Use skillet.
Wash and prepare chicken.
Cook onion and garlic in butter and oil for 5 minutes.
Place chicken in skillet and cook for 40 minutes.
Add the green peppers and tomatoes; cook until the liquid is almost half gone.
Salt and pepper added.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Mix butter or shortening together.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mix.

title: golden harvest casserole
directions: Mix all vegetables and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle parsley and 3 teaspoons ground black pepper over all.
In saucepan combine bouillon, oil, salt, tarragon and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling (correct seasonings, if needed).
Pour over vegetables.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are just tender and still colorful.
Carefully stir vegetables occasionally, but don't lift cover off for very long.

title: sarah's strawberry surprise
directions: Wash berries under cold water.
Remove hulls; drain.
Put berries into a small bowl.
Mash with a potato masher or the rim of a glass.
Set aside 1 cup to beat into meringue.
Sweeten remaining crushed berries to taste with powdered sugar or honey.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites on medium high speed of an electric mixer until they form soft, moist peaks.
Add sugar, about 1 tablespoon at a time, and beating constantly until meringue is thick and glossy.
Add the 1 cup crushed strawberries.
Beat on medium speed just to blend. Transfer meringue mixture to a freezer container.
Cover or wrap well.
Freeze at least 1 hour until solid.
(You can store in freezer up to 1 month.)
To serve, spoon crushed, sweetened to taste berries evenly in the bottom of 4 individual stemmed glasses or shallow dishes.
Top with frozen berry meringue.
Garnish with strawberries and sprigs if desired.
You may use other berries (blueberries, raspberries, etc.).

title: king cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in warm water in a large bowl.

Let stand 5 minutes. Add butter mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour. Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes or until smooth. Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Place in shallow 10 x 15-inch pan which has been lined with foil and generously buttered.
Sprinkle with salt, seasoned pepper and minced onion.
Dot with margarine. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: stir-fried scallops with walnuts and snow peas
directions: Place cornstarch in small bowl; slowly whisk in chicken stock. Whisk in sherry, soy sauce, ginger and red pepper flakes.
Place 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in a wok or nonstick skillet over high heat. When oil is hot, add garlic, scallions and snow peas and stir-fry for 2 minutes until the peas are tender-crisp.
Remove from wok. Add remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil along with scallops and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken stock mixture and cook until slightly thickened, about 1 minute.
Add scallion-snow pea mixture along with walnuts.
Cook and toss about 1 minute longer, taking care not to overcook the scallops.
Serves 4.

title: baked pineapple stuffing garnish
directions: Beat eggs.
Add margarine, sugar and pineapple.
Break bread into 1-inch squares; add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Dresses up all your meats and poultry!

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar, mixing thoroughly.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Put half of the mixed dry ingredients into sugar-oil mixture.
Blend well.
Slowly add remainder of flour mixture, alternating with an egg each time you put part of flour in.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into greased pan, either Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°. Top with Cream Cheese Icing.
Enjoy.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix in order and chill.

title: homemade hot cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Blend in hot water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Stir and heat.
Do not boil. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat with beater until foamy.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding with syrup; add milk and egg.
Blend well.
Add pecans.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool at least 3 hours before cutting.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Beat together cream cheese and 1 teaspoon vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in nuts; set aside.
Cut bread into 10 to 12 (1 1/2-inch) slices; cut a pocket in top of each.
Fill each with 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Beat together eggs, whipping cream, remaining 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and nutmeg.
Using tongs, dip the filled bread slices in egg mixture, being careful not to squeeze out the filling.
Cook on a lightly greased griddle until both sides are golden brown.
To keep cooked slices hot for serving, place them on a baking sheet in a warm oven.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into a medium greased casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Similar to spoon bread.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onions in oil until tender.
Add beef and brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and lasagna.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer.
Cook and drain lasagna; rinse with cold water. Pour a little sauce, lasagna and Ricotta and top with more sauce. Repeat layers two times.
Place Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onions.
Layer in a casserole dish.
In a pan, melt butter and add flour and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper. Add broth and cook until fairly thick.
Pour over potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: dang good pie
directions: Melt butter; mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell; bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until firmly set and brown.

title: meat and macaroni dinner
directions: Cook meat and onion in large skillet until onion is tender. Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly and serve. Serves 4.

title: zucchini bars hors d'oeuvres
directions: Add Bisquick to beaten eggs; stir.
Add remaining ingredients. Gently fold in zucchini.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (preheat oven).
Cut into squares.

title: potato salad
directions: The night or morning before serving, wash and steam or boil the potatoes in their skins.
As they steam or boil, combine vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and grated onion for the marinade.
When potatoes are tender, peel them while they are still hot and dice into the marinade.
Add celery and green pepper; toss lightly so they do not break or become mushy.
Refrigerate.
Add mayonnaise a half hour before serving.
Serves 6.

title: hot fruit drink
directions: Boil the water and cinnamon together for 10 minutes.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Simmer all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Serve hot.
Makes a large recipe.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown meat; chop fine.
Drain.
Add sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Place biscuits in ungreased muffin cups, pressing dough up on sides.
Spoon mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at temperature on biscuit tube until brown.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat oil, garlic and salt in a frying pan.
Add shrimp.
Cook for 5 minutes, until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle parsley over shrimp.
Serves 6.

title: weight loss vegetable soup(low fat - low cholesterol)
directions: Chop all the vegetables. Put into soup pot and cover with water. Boil 10 minutes. Makes 6 quarts.

title: white cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients excluding the beaten egg whites and walnuts. Fold in the egg whites and nuts. Pour into greased and floured 9 X 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes or until cake tests done. Frost with your favorite icing.

title: tuna spinach casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine; blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Heat just to boiling, stirring and cook 1 minute.
Blend in mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add tuna and spinach.
Mix well.
Add cooked noodles.
Spread in ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Prepare 5 quarts of popcorn.
In a 3-quart saucepan, mix syrup, margarine, water, powdered sugar and marshmallows.
Stir over low heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir to coat.
With buttered hands, make into balls.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Beat egg well and then add the other ingredients.
Beat well together and then cook in double boiler over medium heat until clear.

title: scones
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add sugar and rub in butter lightly.
Beat egg and add 3/4 of it to dry ingredients. Add milk to make a fairly soft dough.
Roll out and cut into triangles.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush over with remaining egg.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: louisiana stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add hot water, lemon juice, garlic, bay leaves and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves.
Combine flour and water.
Add to stew, mixing well.
Stir in vegetables and liquid; continue cooking, uncovered, until liquid thickens and vegetables are heated, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Use for vegetable dip.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 325° if using glass pan; 350° if using metal. Dump in pan pie filling, pineapple, cake mix, pecans and coconut. Bake 1 hour. Remember, no mixing.
tags: Thank You brand red cherry pie filling

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cut raw bacon in 1/2-inch pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Saute onion with bacon pieces; drain fat.
Add green beans, mushroom soup and cheese.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts.
Place in a casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: english muffin bread
directions: You will need nonstick cooking spray and three 13 ounce coffee cans.

title: cheesy drop biscuits
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, melted butter, sour cream and Cheddar cheese. Drop by rounded tablespoon 2-inches apart onto a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown. Let cool a few minutes before removing.

title: sweet and sour turkey patties
directions: Combine bread crumbs, chopped onion, salt and 1/2 cup water in bowl; mix well.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in turkey.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown patties in skillet on both sides.
Top with sliced onion.
Combine brown sugar, flour, vinegar, 2 tablespoons water and mustard in small bowl; mix well.
Spoon over patties. Simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.
Yields 6 patties.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Add next 4 ingredients, blending well.
Stir together orange juice and corn syrup; add to crumb mixture.
Blend until moistened.
Press firmly into an 8 1/4 x 4 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pan, lined with aluminum foil; cover tightly.
Store at least 2 days in refrigerator before serving.
Makes one 8-inch loaf.
Cake will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: lobster newburg(eastport, maine-style)
directions: Heat lobster in 6 tablespoons butter.
In another pan, stir flour into 2 tablespoons butter gradually.
Add 2 cups cream; heat.
Stir until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks; stir until thick. Add lobster and season with salt and pepper.
